INSERT INTO `cc_content_content` VALUES (1,9,'1','<h2>Mission</h2>\r\n<p>Our mission is to help bring high impact ideas to life. We are passionate about technology and love the challenge of coming up with simple solutions for complex problems. We have extensive experience helping startups overcome technological and strategical challenges. We love the startup culture and the eco-system.</p>\r\n<h2>How We Work?</h2>\r\n<h3>The Why</h3>\r\n<div>Every startup needs to be sure of this. Because if you don&#39;t know why you are doing it, it doesn&#39;t matter what you do. The &quot;why&quot; is a big factor in your product turning out to be mediocre or amazing. People care about why you do what you do. We can point you in the right direction but you need to figure this one on your own.</div>\r\n<h3>The Who</h3>\r\n<div>We work with entrepreneurs to concretely define their primary, secondary and tertiary target demographic. One of the most important thing is to be absolutely certain who your target market is. The reason is simple if you build for every user on the web, the usefulness of your service and usability goes down drastically. But if you focus on a core set of user types it will translate into a product that would be a lot less complex.</div>\r\n<h3>The What</h3>\r\n<div>Now we are ready to look at what we need to build. We brainstorm an exhaustive list of features with you that could drive the platform forward based on the our target user types. Once we have this list, the time to launch and the budget we can narrow down the exhaustive list to a smaller one that would make the minimum viable product(the MVP) that you could then go and sell to users and investors.</div>\r\n<div>The work we did together in coming up with an exhaustive list is invaluable, it gives us a peek into where we want to take things. This would help us architect the first version that could be easily extended and scaled for the coming iterations. The features would be designed and developed keeping in mind some of the features we intend to add in the future. This could be a huge savings in cost because if not for this step you would be blind sided and might have to refactor a specific feature from scratch just because we had no idea about what was coming in the future.</div>\r\n<h3>The Numbers</h3>\r\n<div>Keeping score and seeing how you are doing is critical to improve what we build. Getting feedback from users and observing how they react and use the system becomes helps us iterate over the next few versions and build something that your target users and investors would be happier about. We help you make sense of the data and stay away from vanity metrics.</div>\r\n<h2>What Can We Help With?</h2>\r\n<p>We can help you with web development, strategy, technology evaluation, user experience/usability and testing.</p>','2013-03-22 07:28:17','2014-09-05 16:39:47','','','About Us','com.cc.content.page.Page',NULL,'2013-03-22 07:28:17',NULL,NULL),(2,4,'1','<address><strong>CauseCode Technologies Pvt Ltd</strong><br>Office 3, 2nd Floor, Revati Arcade 2, Baner Road, Baner,<br> Pune, MH 411045<br> <abbr title=\"Email\">Email:</abbr> bootstrap@causecode.com<p>&nbsp;</p></address><p><img data-mce-p-src=\"https://maps.google.co.in/maps?f=q&amp;source=s_q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=CauseCode+Technologies+Pvt+Ltd,+Baner,+Pune,+Maharashtra&amp;aq=0&amp;oq=causecode&amp;sll=18.565536,73.776047&amp;sspn=0.001414,0.002642&amp;vpsrc=6&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=CauseCode+Technologies+Pvt+Ltd,&amp;hnear=Baner,+Pune,+Maharashtra&amp;ll=18.565608,73.776243&amp;spn=0.01309,0.008128&amp;t=m&amp;output=embed\" data-mce-p-scrolling=\"no\" data-mce-p-marginwidth=\"0\" data-mce-p-marginheight=\"0\" data-mce-p-frameborder=\"0\" width=\"425\" height=\"350\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" data-mce-object=\"iframe\" class=\"mce-object mce-object-iframe\"><br> <small><a href=\"https://maps.google.co.in/maps?f=q&amp;source=embed&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=CauseCode+Technologies+Pvt+Ltd,+Baner,+Pune,+Maharashtra&amp;aq=0&amp;oq=causecode&amp;sll=18.565536,73.776047&amp;sspn=0.001414,0.002642&amp;vpsrc=6&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=CauseCode+Technologies+Pvt+Ltd,&amp;hnear=Baner,+Pune,+Maharashtra&amp;ll=18.565608,73.776243&amp;spn=0.01309,0.008128&amp;t=m\" style=\"color: #0000ff; text-align: left;\" data-mce-href=\"https://maps.google.co.in/maps?f=q&amp;source=embed&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=CauseCode+Technologies+Pvt+Ltd,+Baner,+Pune,+Maharashtra&amp;aq=0&amp;oq=causecode&amp;sll=18.565536,73.776047&amp;sspn=0.001414,0.002642&amp;vpsrc=6&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=CauseCode+Technologies+Pvt+Ltd,&amp;hnear=Baner,+Pune,+Maharashtra&amp;ll=18.565608,73.776243&amp;spn=0.01309,0.008128&amp;t=m\" data-mce-style=\"color: #0000ff; text-align: left;\">View Larger Map</a></small></p>','2013-04-02 09:51:18','2015-10-10 12:14:02','','','Contact Us','com.cc.content.page.Page',NULL,'2013-04-02 09:51:18',NULL,NULL),(3,6,'1','<div class=\"media-body media\">\r\n	<h2 itemprop=\"name\">\r\n		Would 500 Hours of Free Coding Get Your Startup Off the Ground?</h2>\r\n	<p>\r\n		<span>Northeastern alumnus Vishesh Duggar wants to help get your idea off the ground by giving your startup the most precious commodity in the entrepreneurial world: Time. One lucky startup will be awarded 500 hours of work from his incubator, appropriately called 500Hrs, to flesh out and build a minimum viable product (MVP) for free. <a href=\"http://bostinno.streetwise.co/2013/10/22/boston-startups-would-500-hoursof-free-coding-help-your-startup/\">Read more.</a></span></p>\r\n	<h2>\r\n		Accelerator gives away 500 hours of tech development to discover next big thing</h2>\r\n	<p>\r\n		The UpTake: 500Hrs founder and developer Vishesh Duggar is tweaking the accelerator model to help solve a big problem facing early-stage startups, technology development.<a href=\"http://upstart.bizjournals.com/companies/hatched/2013/10/24/500-hrs-launches-new-accelerator-model.html\"> Read more.</a></p>\r\n	<h2>\r\n		Indian Startup 500 Hours, Giving Away 500 Development Hours To Worthy Startups</h2>\r\n	<div class=\"media-body media\">\r\n		We&#39;ve been working with startups for the last 4 years and the biggest problem that We&#39;ve come across is the lack of funding to build something that they can use to get funded or attract customers. We will reduce the cost of building the MVP to close to zero and provide tech mentorship to startups, giving them a better shot at succeeding.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://nibletz.com/2013/04/11/indian-startup-500-hours-giving-500-development-hours-worthy-startups-interview/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"View article on nibletz.com\">Read more</a></div>\r\n	<p>\r\n		&nbsp;</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		&nbsp;</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		&nbsp;</p>\r\n	<p>\r\n		&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n','2013-04-16 02:40:16','2013-10-25 18:32:38','',NULL,'Press','com.cc.content.page.Page',NULL,'2013-04-16 02:40:16',NULL,NULL),(4,7,'1','<p>\r\n	It all started with a question, &ldquo;Are we making a difference?&rdquo;. Since then this is a question that I ask myself more often when evaluating our progress.</p>\n<div>\r\n	I had co-founded a consulting company in Boston with a couple other friends whom I had collaborated with on another startup during my Masters in 2008. We helped entities like the The Entrepreneurship Center at MIT, MassChallenge and other small businesses. I wanted to transition us into a product company eventually, as <a href=\"http://blog.guykawasaki.com/2006/01/the_art_of_boot.html\" target=\"_blank\">Guy Kawasaki</a> suggested I too believed in bootstrapping it without outside funding and believed consulting could fund what we do as a product.</div>\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\r\n	We were cash flow positive and we could even scrape through a decent enough pay check. The answer to the question, &ldquo;Are we making a difference?&rdquo; was &ldquo;Not enough&rdquo;.</div>\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\r\n	And so CauseCode was born in 2011 the ultimate goal was no longer to become a product company but a mission to help make high impact ideas a reality. For the last two and a half years we have helped half a dozen entities. The road has been long and hard. I had never hired people let alone fire them, I had to learn about other aspects of business like marketing, hiring, branding and the toughest of all frequently stop being the introvert that I am and project the extrovert person people expect a head of the company to be. But in the end this is all worth it because we are helping build startups that will change volunteering, help people with addiction issues and track their habits to get to the bottom of what affects their mood, behaviour and health.</div>\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\r\n	Like most startups and small companies the two biggest problems at our hand to grow at faster rate were hiring and business development. It was too time consuming to find and hire the right people. People who believed that they could make a difference, people who were passionate about technology as we were and who took pride in what they produced. Not many knew of us in the world. Which meant top talent wasn&#39;t going to come looking for us! We had to work with colleges and sift through applicants to build our team which wasn&#39;t as effective as people looking to work for you.</div>\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\r\n	And then there was getting work that excited you with a client that you would enjoy working with. We have reached out to more than 160 startups and talked to a little more than 50 and exciting work and great teams seldom come together. We did end up helping a few interesting startups as mentioned above. But the rate at which things were moving was something we were not completely happy about. The answer to the question, &ldquo;Are we making a difference?&rdquo; earlier this year was, &ldquo;not enough&rdquo;.</div>\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\r\n	What we also discovered was that most of the startups that we wanted to work with didn&#39;t have the money to hire us. They wanted to work with us if not for the funding situation. And there were few we wanted to be a part of. I felt there should be a better way to approach this so that could ease this pain for them. We have tried extending a credit line, deferred payment, equity and host of other barter options but those still were adding to the cost for startups some way or the other. One day browsing the web it hit me, the VC companies already have a solution to this problem! They organize/fund accelerators to weed out high impact ideas and teams. Voila! yes I thought we could invite startups to apply. We give the winning teams close to 500 hrs of consulting time.&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\n<div>\r\n	500Hrs is fundamentally going to change how startups lacking tech founders approach doing startups. You can read more about the program <a href=\"http://www.causecode.com/500Hrs\">here</a>.</div>','2013-09-19 11:09:43','2015-08-22 10:15:33','','The beginning','500Hrs: Origins','com.cc.content.blog.Blog',NULL,'2013-09-19 11:09:43',NULL,NULL),(5,6,'1','<p>\r\n	I will go over how you can wrap an HTML5 mobile site into an Android app. You will have your Android app in less than an hour!</p>\n<p>\r\n	Most of you stumbling on this would dipping their feet in Phone gap for the first time or have very little experience. First things first. I need to give out a brief clarification about PhoneGap vs. Cordova. Adobe which owned and started the PhoneGap project donated its codebase to Apache foundation and the project was named Cordova. PhoneGap in its current form is another distribution of Cordova. Which will allow Cordova to be independent and open source and allow Adobe to implement integration and dependence with other Adobe technologies into PhoneGap.</p>\n<h2>\r\n	Install</h2>\n<p>\r\n	Install PhoneGap 3, prerequisite node.js. More info here You will also have to install Android SDK.</p>\n<h2>\r\n	Create a project</h2>\n<p>\r\n	You can create a project by giving a directory name, package and the default activity class phonegap create hello com.example.hello HelloWorld</p>\n<h2>\r\n	Add Android Platform</h2>\n<p>\r\n	The above would have created a project in the folder named hello, change directory to hello The following command would add Android specific code to the project phonegap build android</p>\n<h2>\r\n	PhoneGap Configuration</h2>\n<h3>\r\n	Config.xml</h3>\n<p>\r\n	Edit <project dir=\"\">/www/config.xml Change access origin to &ldquo;*&rdquo; or &ldquo;http://yourdomain.com&rdquo;<br />\r\n	<code>&lt;access origin=&quot;*&quot;&gt; &lt;/access&gt;</code></project></p>\n<h3>\r\n	Main.xml</h3>\n<p>\r\n	Edit &lt;project dir&gt;/platforms/android/res/layout/main.xml</p>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot; encoding=&quot;utf-8&quot;?&gt;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&lt;FrameLayout xmlns:android=&quot;http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android&quot;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; android:layout_width=&quot;fill_parent&quot;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; android:layout_height=&quot;fill_parent&quot;&gt;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;org.apache.cordova.CordovaWebView&nbsp;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; android:layout_width=&quot;fill_parent&quot;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; android:layout_height=&quot;fill_parent&quot;&nbsp;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; android:id = &quot;@+id/mainView&quot;/&gt;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&lt;/FrameLayout&gt;</code></div>\n<h3>\r\n	HelloWorld.java</h3>\n<p>\r\n	Edit <project dir=\"\">/platforms/android/src/com/example/hello/HelloWorld.java</project></p>\n<div>\r\n	<code>/*</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Licensed to the Apache Software Foundation (ASF) under one</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;or more contributor license agreements. &nbsp;See the NOTICE file</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;distributed with this work for additional information</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;regarding copyright ownership. &nbsp;The ASF licenses this file</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;to you under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&quot;License&quot;); you may not use this file except in compliance</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;with the License. &nbsp;You may obtain a copy of the License at</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing,</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;software distributed under the License is distributed on an</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&quot;AS IS&quot; BASIS, WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;KIND, either express or implied. &nbsp;See the License for the</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;specific language governing permissions and limitations</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;under the License.</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp;*/</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>package com.example.hello;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>import android.os.Bundle;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>import org.apache.cordova.*;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>import java.util.concurrent.ExecutorService;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>import java.util.concurrent.Executors;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>import org.apache.cordova.CordovaInterface;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>import org.apache.cordova.CordovaPlugin;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>import org.apache.cordova.LOG;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>import org.json.JSONException;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>import org.json.JSONObject;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>import android.annotation.SuppressLint;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>import android.app.*;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>import android.util.Log;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>import android.view.*;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>import android.content.Intent;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>public class HelloWorld extends Activity implements CordovaInterface {</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; CordovaWebView cwv;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; private final ExecutorService threadPool = Executors.newCachedThreadPool();</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; private int activityState = 0; &nbsp;// 0=starting, 1=running (after 1st resume), 2=shutting down</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; // Plugin to call when activity result is received</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; protected CordovaPlugin activityResultCallback = null;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; protected boolean activityResultKeepRunning;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; private static final String TAG = &quot;HelloWorld&quot;;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; /*</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;* The variables below are used to cache some of the activity properties.</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;*/</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; // Keep app running when pause is received. (default = true)</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; // If true, then the JavaScript and native code continue to run in the background</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; // when another application (activity) is started.</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; protected boolean keepRunning = true;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; @Override</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; public void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState)</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; {</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);&nbsp;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; setContentView(R.layout.main);</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; cwv = (CordovaWebView) this.findViewById(R.id.mainView);</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Config.init(this);</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>Log.v(TAG, &quot;Trying to load http://causecode.com&quot;);</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; cwv.loadUrl(&quot;http://causecode.com&quot;,60000);</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; }</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; /**</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;* Launch an activity for which you would like a result when it finished. When this activity exits,</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;* your onActivityResult() method will be called.</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;*</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;* @param command &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; The command object</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;* @param intent &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The intent to start</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;* @param requestCode &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; The request code that is passed to callback to identify the activity</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;*/</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; public void startActivityForResult(CordovaPlugin command, Intent intent, int requestCode) {</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; this.activityResultCallback = command;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; this.activityResultKeepRunning = this.keepRunning;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; // If multitasking turned on, then disable it for activities that return results</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; if (command != null) {</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; this.keepRunning = false;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; }</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; // Start activity</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; super.startActivityForResult(intent, requestCode);</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; }</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; public void setActivityResultCallback(CordovaPlugin plugin) {</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; this.activityResultCallback = plugin;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; }</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; /**</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;* Get the Android activity.</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;*</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;* @return</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;*/</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; public Activity getActivity() {</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; return this;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; }</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp;</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;/**</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;* Called when a message is sent to plugin.</code></div>\n<div>\r\n	<code>&nbs