olestias excepturi sint occaecati cupiditate non provident, similique sunt ',NULL,2,'2013-10-21 09:52:56','2013-10-21 09:52:56',16),(77,0,'At vero eos et accusamus et iusto odio dignissimos ducimus qui blanditiis praesentium voluptatum deleniti atque corrupti quos dolores et quas molestias excepturi sint occaecati cupiditate non provident, similique sunt ',NULL,2,'2013-10-21 09:52:59','2013-10-21 09:52:59',14),(78,0,'2',NULL,2,'2013-10-21 09:53:34','2013-10-21 09:53:34',18),(79,2,'http://laxmi.com',NULL,2,'2013-10-21 09:53:39','2013-10-21 09:54:59',19),(80,3,'0',NULL,2,'2013-10-21 09:56:04','2013-10-21 09:56:14',20),(81,3,'Our \"managed\" crowdfunding approach enables creators to focus on doing what they love... creating awesome stuff, while leaving the hassles of printing, fulfillment and customer service to us. There are a few \"similar\" platforms, all of which are focused specifically on t-shirt crowdfunding. We will allow creators to submit a much broader range of \"printable\" products, including posters, greeting cards, comic books, playing cards, apparel, calendars, iphone/ipad cases, stickers and more.',NULL,13,'2013-10-22 00:12:41','2013-10-22 01:09:51',3),(82,4,'In addition to giving artists the ability to do what they love, without having to deal with the annoying production and shipping stuff... there are geographical boundaries to crowdfunding we hope to eliminate. It\'s impossible for a artist based out of India to run a kickstarter campaign where the rewards would need to be sent to backers in the US. We eliminate these boundaries since the artist can submit their digital art from anywhere and production/fulfilment is centralized in the US.',NULL,13,'2013-10-22 00:27:35','2013-10-22 02:02:20',4),(83,1,'CrowdImpress is a \"Managed\" Crowdfunding Portal for Artists, Designers and Photographers to create and promote awesome \"printable\" products that are funded by the crowd, then printed and shipped directly by our team. Creators earn up to a 50% share of the project funding, without any of the hassles and risks of current \"DIY\" crowdfunding platforms. Backers get quality products, delivered on time, with complete accountability and a 100% happiness guarantee.',NULL,13,'2013-10-22 01:06:24','2013-10-22 01:11:21',1),(84,2,'I came to work for my family-owned printing business 12 years ago. The commercial printing industry began to falter in the late-2000s, so in 2010 I started to look for alternative business models to grow our company. Last year I became enthralled with kickstarter and began to back some projects, specifically projects with a \"print\" element to them. I noticed a trend of project creators struggling with printing, packing and shipping during their campaign, activities that most of them had little or no experience dealing with. Projects were being delayed by weeks or months due to these issues, backers were getting frustrated and looking for answers, creators were struggling to respond. So one day thought to myself \"I deal with these issues every day at my business... what if there was a way to let these talented artists just focus on creating cool stuff and allow someone else to take care of the annoying production, shipping and customer service. The idea for CrowdImpress was born!',NULL,13,'2013-10-22 01:07:16','2013-10-22 01:45:32',2),(85,0,'Yes',NULL,13,'2013-10-22 02:02:20','2013-10-22 02:02:20',5),(86,0,'Attracting talented creators will be the key to success. Each creator has 100s (sometimes 1000s) of friends, family, fans and followers they will promote their projects to. We will discover and leverage online communities that these creators are on. as well as provide tools and resources to help creators make their projects more successful. Our approach will be a combination of inbound marketing and online advertising to attract creators who will in turn drive traffic to their projects.',NULL,13,'2013-10-22 02:20:32','2013-10-22 02:20:32',6),(87,1,'We are not developers. Although I have built several websites personally and for clients, it has always been using a CMS platform and the type of coding needed for this type of project is beyond my abilities. This leads to us having to hire a company to develop the site, which leads to problem #2; getting funding to develop the site. The last problem I see is conveying my vision to the developers',NULL,13,'2013-10-22 02:24:43','2013-10-22 02:49:59',7),(88,1,'We are currently consulting with a local developer. No actual development has started yet, but they are creating a \"functional specifications document\" along with some coding specifications that can then be used as the blueprint for the company we would hire to develop the site (whether it is them or another company). After several conversations with developers, we decided to take this step as way to fully realize our vision and make sure the site will be developed in a way that supports both our current and future plans. We believe this will solve the problem I mentioned above regarding conveying my vision. We have committed $10,000 to this strategy consulting, and felt it was necessary to be able to accurately plan a budget for the development of the site. We hope by doing this, we will know exactly what it will take to get to MVP, then V2 and beyond without having to deal with unplanned costs or expenses because we weren\'t on the same page as the developer.\n\nIn terms of getting funding, we do have some access via our current business as well as friends/family. The startup ecosystem has become very active here in St. Louis, so there is also the possibility of getting outside funding but I prefer to bootstrap/self-fund for as long as possible to avoid diluting our equity. We are confident that if done right, our model will find success and prefer to be in complete control until we have fully validated our model.',NULL,13,'2013-10-22 02:32:03','2013-10-22 02:40:04',8),(89,1,'April 2013',NULL,13,'2013-10-22 02:40:29','2013-10-22 02:41:33',10),(90,1,'June 2013',NULL,13,'2013-10-22 02:41:14','2013-10-22 02:42:51',11),(91,2,'We would like to be able to roll out an MVP version of the site in early 2014 and hope to see about 500 funded projects and roughly $1m in gross revenue by the end of the year. By late 2014 we would like to roll out V2 which will include an Ecommerce marketplace to purchase successfully funded items on-demand from an inventory of overruns that will will be storing. V2 also includes an incentive program for creators that tracks and rewards creators based on popularity and success so that we can encourage successful creators to continue to be active on the site. The next phase (V3?) would likely bring functionality for organizations or brands so that a company or not-for-profit could \"sponsor\" or \"curate\" projects that would be created under their brand guidelines and funding would be shared with creators. We hope to see another 1200+ projects funded during year 2 with $2m-$2.5m gross revenue. Although not fully mapped out yet, the third year would possibly bring items beyond ones that are simply \"printable\" or maybe 3D printing along with tools for creating the art online using the platform. We estimate that we would see 2500+ successfully funded projects the third year with about $4m-$5m in revenue. As a comparison, Teespring.com which is the similar t-shirt funding model I mentioned earlier, is averaging $750k per month just with t-shirts. Of course the long term goal is to be acquired by a company like zazzle, vistaprint or cafepress for millions, but we have not set a timeline on our exit plan.',NULL,13,'2013-10-22 02:49:48','2013-10-22 03:03:21',9),(92,0,'No',NULL,13,'2013-10-22 03:03:41','2013-10-22 03:03:41',12),(93,2,'No',NULL,13,'2013-10-22 03:03:44','2013-10-22 03:03:58',13),(94,1,'Maybe for like $40-$50',NULL,13,'2013-10-22 03:03:58','2013-10-22 03:04:16',14),(95,0,'400-500 hours (just a guess, honestly have no idea)',NULL,13,'2013-10-22 03:06:09','2013-10-22 03:06:09',16),(96,0,'$50,000-$60,000',NULL,13,'2013-10-22 03:06:53','2013-10-22 03:06:53',15),(97,0,'0',NULL,13,'2013-10-22 03:06:58','2013-10-22 03:06:58',20),(98,0,'0',NULL,13,'2013-10-22 03:07:10','2013-10-22 03:07:10',18),(99,0,'0',NULL,13,'2013-10-22 03:07:44','2013-10-22 03:07:44',17),(100,7,'Kampus is a social network that enables college students to interact exclusively with others attending the same school through diverse, useful, and entertaining features. Those features include:\nA marketplace,\nA live feed section,\nA directory,\nA flyers section,\nA professors section,\nA chat section,\nA dating section,\nA memes section,\nA deals section that lists deals from businesses located around the school, which will be the main component of our business model.',NULL,10,'2013-10-22 07:10:18','2013-10-23 04:42:01',1),(101,1,'We are a pair of international students from Honduras attending Lindenwood University in Saint Charles, Missouri. Diego Kafie will graduate in May 2014 with a double major in Marketing and International Business, while Alcides Zelaya will graduate in May 2014 with a major in Computer Science and a minor in Business Administration. We are both tech enthusiasts, and as such, we\'re extremely motivated to create a product of our own. We\'ve been working on Kampus for 6 months and are extremely proud of all we have accomplished. Our hope is that once we graduate, we can move on to working on Kampus full time. Recently, we made it to the top 25 finalists for Capital Innovators, a startup incubator in St. Louis, Missouri. \nWe aren\'t going anywhere but up, and we\'re looking for help to gain momentum and launch Kampus into the successful business we know it can be!',NULL,10,'2013-10-22 07:17:42','2013-10-22 07:33:17',2),(102,5,'What makes Kampus unique and different is the exclusivity it will offer students, and how it will be a place to solely interact with people from the same college campus. It will also differ from any other social network because of the wide variety of features it will offer in one place, saving students the time from jumping to several sites to enjoy similar (yet not completely exclusive) features. Also, Kampus will aid in getting exclusive deals for students, helping them save money.',NULL,10,'2013-10-22 07:20:53','2013-10-23 04:44:24',3),(103,0,'Yes',NULL,10,'2013-10-22 07:20:54','2013-10-22 07:20:54',5),(104,5,'Students are looking for ways to interact with others that attend their same school, but are having a hard time finding the right solution. Most people create Facebook groups and try to get everyone on them. Also, students have very little money to spend. With the deals section, we will get students much-needed discounts specifically made for them. We are including these features, and many more, into one very complete and clean app that will satisfy every student\'s needs.',NULL,10,'2013-10-22 07:25:28','2013-10-22 19:17:55',4),(105,1,'We plan on getting users by several different alternatives. Right after launch, we plan on posting about ourselves in college student Facebook groups, offering our download links for their devices. Once these people download the app, they will have the opportunity to share Kampus with their friends from inside the app, creating a domino effect. Further down the road, we plan on buying Facebook ads to appear on potential users\' screens as a \"Suggested App\" on their mobile Facebook pages.',NULL,10,'2013-10-22 11:04:52','2013-10-22 19:18:12',6),(106,0,'April 2013.',NULL,10,'2013-10-22 11:05:20','2013-10-22 11:05:20',10),(107,0,'Right after we polished the idea in our heads.',NULL,10,'2013-10-22 11:05:48','2013-10-22 11:05:48',11),(108,0,'1. Not enough time. Until we graduate, we can\'t work on Kampus full time, and that is slowing us down.\n2. Only one developer. Alcides is the only developer working on Kampus. If we had two brains working on it, things would get done twice as fast.\n3. Trouble with numbers. We are having trouble with the pricing scales for the business model. We don\'t want to underprice or overprice.',NULL,10,'2013-10-22 18:50:37','2013-10-22 18:50:37',7),(109,2,'1. As soon as we graduate, our time will free itself. Winning 500Hrs will also help in speeding up the development process.\n2. Hopefully, 500Hrs will aid with our need for more developers as well. 500 hours is a lot of time to work on a project, and it might be enough to solve our need. However, we are also looking to hiring another developer further down the road, as soon as we\'re generating enough revenue to afford it.\n3. We are planning to solve our problem with numbers through two different methods. First, we are part of a network called ITEN in St. Louis, and they have a large group of advisors and different programs that will help us polish our numbers. Also, we plan on using our school, Lindenwood University, as our test market and trying out different price scales to see how well they perform. Taking that information, we will create the final pricing strategy to roll out to the entirety of our campuses.',NULL,10,'2013-10-22 19:01:02','2013-10-23 04:46:48',8),(110,2,'After May, we plan on working on Kampus full time. Our launch process will start locally, targeting the big schools in the St. Louis area. We plan on gradually expanding from there. Hopefully, by May 2015 we will be generating enough revenue from the deals section to invest in paid Facebook ads and roll out a more aggressive customer acquisition strategy. We will exponentially make more revenue as more schools are added and more businesses are enlisted, and thus we\'ll be able to hire more employees. These employees will work to expand our roster of businesses by making calls and contacting potential businesses that might be willing to use our app to attract student customers. The remaining time in the 3 year period will likely be dedicated to getting Kampus on the phones of college students all across the country, while working to attract even more local businesses to offer their deals through our app to their nearby college campus.',NULL,10,'2013-10-22 19:01:10','2013-10-23 04:47:13',9),(111,0,'Yes',NULL,10,'2013-10-22 19:01:24','2013-10-22 19:01:24',12),(112,1,'Yes',NULL,10,'2013-10-22 19:01:37','2013-10-22 19:03:19',13),(113,2,'250 hours.',NULL,10,'2013-10-22 19:02:28','2013-10-22 19:02:39',16),(114,0,'$2000.',NULL,10,'2013-10-22 19:02:56','2013-10-22 19:02:56',15),(115,1,'$50 or less.',NULL,10,'2013-10-22 19:03:17','2013-10-22 19:03:25',14),(116,0,'0',NULL,10,'2013-10-22 19:03:34','2013-10-22 19:03:34',20),(117,0,'1.',NULL,10,'2013-10-22 19:03:47','2013-10-22 19:03:47',18),(118,0,'0.',NULL,10,'2013-10-22 19:03:49','2013-10-22 19:03:49',17),(119,0,'We want to create Kampus because as part of the target market ourselves, we understand there is a need for a product just like this. We want to help students connect with their fellow classmates and neighbors, and we feel that Kampus will do that and much more!\nAs tech enthusiasts, we want to leave our mark in the world by creating a product of our own that people can enjoy for many years to come. We can\'t imagine anything more fulfilling than launching a successful app into the world! ',NULL,10,'2013-10-22 19:05:56','2013-10-22 19:05:56',21),(120,1,'Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Etiam tortor augue, cursus sed luctus a, laoreet Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Etiam tortor augue, cursus sed luctus a, laoreet ',NULL,19,'2013-10-22 22:59:28','2013-11-14 13:35:08',1),(121,4,'Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Etiam tortor augue, cursus sed luctus a, laoreet                                                                                                                             a',NULL,19,'2013-10-22 23:01:06','2013-11-14 13:34:55',2),(122,3,'Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Etiam tortor augue, cursus sed luctus a, laoreet                                                                  