luctus a, laoreet ',NULL,19,'2013-10-23 01:03:43','2013-11-14 13:35:30',14),(136,0,'Ive spoken with some devs and based of current OpenSource libraries about 300-400hrs',NULL,19,'2013-10-23 01:03:45','2013-10-23 01:03:45',16),(137,1,'Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Etiam tortor augue, cursus sed luctus a, laoreet ',NULL,19,'2013-10-23 01:03:48','2013-11-14 13:35:32',15),(138,1,'Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Etiam tortor augue, cursus sed luctus a, laoreet Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Etiam tortor augue, cursus sed luctus a, laoreet ',NULL,19,'2013-10-23 01:07:14','2013-11-14 13:35:44',21),(139,1,'1',NULL,11,'2013-10-23 09:28:52','2013-11-17 12:14:32',17),(140,0,'Yes',NULL,11,'2013-10-23 09:29:08','2013-10-23 09:29:08',12),(141,1,'We\'re eliminating complexity and creepiness out of location sharing.\n\nShare with a simple text. In as little as 3 steps you can:\n- find your friends at a crowded place or event in realtime\n- share where you are if youre running late\n- help a family member whos lost get back in the right direction\n\nYougy is like the Dropbox of mobile location sharing:\n- its insanely simple to use\n- your friends dont have download the app for you to share with them\n- privacy is super simple',NULL,23,'2013-10-23 23:49:09','2013-10-23 18:22:09',1),(142,0,'We were meeting with family at the zoo on a crowded day and the conversation went like this: \n[Ian] Hey, we\'re here. Where are you guys?\n[Tyler] We\'re here by the pond seating area.\n[I] Ok, I see a seating area but not you.\n[T] I\'m standing across from a clock tower-looking thing. I\'m waiving my arms.\n[I] Still nothing.\n[T] Ok, are you facing away or toward the clock tower?... never mind, I\'ll come to the entrance to find you.\n[T] Wait... what entrance did you come in at?\n\nAfter 10-15 minutes of explaining what we\'re standing by, wandering around, , sharing screenshots of Google Maps and trying to get Latitude to work we decided it was time to build something on our own.\n\nWe had been looking for months for a simple service to share in realtime that didn\'t make us worry if all our Gmail contacts could see us. We also wanted something easy enough for our moms to use. We couldn\'t find anything and so the zoo incident was our sign to build our own.',NULL,23,'2013-10-23 18:30:32','2013-10-23 18:30:32',2),(143,2,'Yougy is the only app that allows is all these at once:\n- Realtime\n- Works in the browser as well as a lightweight app (no need to download to use/share)\n- Allows for multiple users without managing setup or circles\n- Privacy and sharing is as manageable as Google Docs\n- Free\n- Promising future features that won\'t bloat or add complexity to sharing as easy as a text.\n\nIn in Alpha the #1 reason it\'s different is because it\'s so insanely simple to use.',NULL,23,'2013-10-24 05:31:21','2013-10-23 18:47:59',3),(144,0,'We\'re solving 2 high-level problems:\n- Uncertainty\n- Complexity\n\n* Uncertainty\nWhen you\'re waiting for someone to meet you at a specific place you just want to know immediately \"where are they?\". You really don\'t care about much more than \"have they even left yet?\" \"are they on their way?\". In queue theory, uncertainty is the #1 cause of frustration and we address that head on.\n\n* Complexity\n',NULL,23,'2013-10-23 18:53:29','2013-10-23 18:53:29',4),(145,1,'No',NULL,23,'2013-10-23 18:53:35','2013-10-23 18:53:36',5),(146,2,'[Let us clarify the previous answer first: We have a plan but explain it our pitch deck... http://www.bothsidesofthetable.com/2009/11/03/are-business-plans-still-necessary/]\n\n1) Virality is built-in to the app -- You don\'t need the app to share/receive location, you can share in as little as 3 taps.\n2) Following Dave McClure\'s AARRR tactics with a mix of inbound, growth hacking and traditional marketing\n3) Partnerships with national and local organizations/events we\'ve identified.\n',NULL,23,'2013-10-23 18:57:21','2013-10-24 18:29:00',6),(147,0,'No',NULL,11,'2013-10-23 23:14:39','2013-10-23 23:14:39',5),(148,2,'NABR helps you discover and share crowd-sourced and geographically relevant events anywhere in the world at the hyper-local level and in real-time. Our simple mobile helps you discover relevant events in different neighborhoods, and if you see a relevant event, with one snap of a camera phone you can share it to the neighborhood for others to enjoy. It\'s a win-win situation for the event, business and community as we make great events discoverable. ',NULL,25,'2013-10-24 02:31:30','2013-10-24 02:43:20',1),(149,1,'As a team of transplants to a new city, we often found that meaningful and intruguing activities and events were scattered and hard to find. We developed NABR with this in mind. NABR helps you discover crowd-sourced, geographically relevant, and meaningful events in real-time. If you see a cool event promotion and want to share it, then with one click of your camera phone an event can be digitized and anonymously posted to your NABRhood alongside your existing social networks if you so choose.\n\nThe positivity of sharing builds as the community-based event/business/artist enjoys better promotion, you have a better outlet to see who is interested in joining you at that event, and the every NABR has a better way to find out all the interesting things happening in their NABRhood.',NULL,25,'2013-10-24 02:32:15','2013-10-24 02:40:53',2),(150,2,'So what makes NABR different from a social app like Facebook? Where the Facebook market is saturated with invites to games, functions, private events, and public events that blend everything together, NABR would make it possible to make the distinction of limited local events that are relevant to ones NABR-hood and interest. In addition, a user can use their existing social profile (Facebook/Twitter/Instagram) to invite others to join, alongside posting on the native NABR network.  ',NULL,25,'2013-10-24 02:44:17','2013-10-24 02:51:25',3),(151,3,'Facebook connects friends, Linkedin connects professionals, Twitter connects the world and so on.  NABR was created to connect neighborhoods. Whether you are a life-long resident, a transplant or a tourist just looking for something to do, NABR provides value. We are transplants to St. Louis ourselves who fell in love with the city. We just simply noticed that unique, geographically relevant, and community-enhancing events were hard to find - now we want to fix it for the world. ',NULL,25,'2013-10-24 02:45:58','2013-10-24 02:49:51',4),(152,0,'Yes',NULL,25,'2013-10-24 02:49:51','2013-10-24 02:49:51',5),(153,1,'As we have done our research, we have seen a MASSIVE need for a platform such as NABR on the college campus setting. In addition connecting local business to neighborhoods With these two target customers in mind, we have developed a strategy as follows: Campus - be the platform for students,organizations and universities to post and find events. 2. Neighborhoods - partner with local businesses to promote events via NABR and engage customers. ',NULL,25,'2013-10-24 02:56:16','2013-10-24 02:57:01',6),(154,0,'1. Building an iOS platform.\n2. Building a web platform for paying clients.\n3. Finding talent/money to build the above needs.',NULL,25,'2013-10-24 02:58:16','2013-10-24 02:58:16',7),(155,1,'We have currently built an MVP version of NABR in Android. We have spoken to 80+ client and have 200 users in closed Beta testing using the app and providing us feedback. We have received extremely positive feedback to this point. We have also noticed that our target market of college students is iOS centric and we need to build the MVP version for them. In addition, we have several clients who need a web based platform to mobilize their event portfolios onto NABR. As we continue to polish the Android version, we are simply',NULL,25,'2013-10-24 02:59:46','2013-10-24 03:02:16',8),(156,0,'0',NULL,19,'2013-10-24 17:08:06','2013-10-24 17:08:06',17),(157,0,'February 2013',NULL,23,'2013-10-24 18:29:10','2013-10-24 18:29:10',11),(158,0,'1) TIME.\nWe both work >50hrs/wk day jobs and have young kids. Time is limited and working between 10pm-8am sucks.\nTo get more time we need capital. To get capital we need traction. To get traction we need to get a beta out.',NULL,23,'2013-10-24 18:32:24','2013-10-24 18:32:24',7),(159,0,'One founder focuses on all aspects of business (applications like 500hrs, competitions, fundraising, legal, future partnerships, pitch decks, etc.) while the other founder works solely on product. But now that we\'re in bug squashing mode (and having to fix public libraries), things have slowed down more. We\'re in the process of securing capital to go fulltime and build out the app faster.',NULL,23,'2013-10-24 18:34:56','2013-10-24 18:34:56',8),(160,2,'* Funding by Q4 2013\n* Public beta for Android + Web by Q1 2014\n* iPhone beta Q2 2014\n* 1 million users by Q1 2015\n  Raise Series A\n  Hire 1st employee\n* Monetization testing Q2 2015\n* 2 million users by Q3 2015\n* 10 million users by Q2 2016\n\nOur complete product road map includes many more improvements and partnerships between 2013 and 2015, but these are the larger milestones.',NULL,23,'2013-10-24 18:35:21','2013-10-24 18:56:57',9),(161,1,'2012',NULL,23,'2013-10-24 18:48:15','2013-10-24 18:49:30',10),(162,0,'Yes',NULL,23,'2013-10-24 18:57:03','2013-10-24 18:57:03',12),(163,0,'No',NULL,23,'2013-10-24 18:57:08','2013-10-24 18:57:08',13),(164,0,'10',NULL,23,'2013-10-24 18:57:19','2013-10-24 18:57:19',14),(165,2,'300',NULL,23,'2013-10-24 18:57:42','2013-10-24 19:00:11',16),(166,0,'$500',NULL,23,'2013-10-24 19:00:44','2013-10-24 19:00:44',15),(167,0,'0',NULL,23,'2013-10-24 19:01:01','2013-10-24 19:01:01',20),(168,0,'1',NULL,23,'2013-10-24 19:01:11','2013-10-24 19:01:11',18),(169,0,'* We believe in simple, that solve everyday problems that can scale big. We want to develop powerful products that a mom or child can use.\n* We see a need in the market and no one has solved it /properly/ in the last 5 years. \n* I would rather pursue this startup even though the risk is high than advance my current career (which is safe). I can\'t imagine doing anything else. ',NULL,23,'2013-10-24 19:04:15','2013-10-24 19:04:15',21),(170,0,'In the next three years we are confident in creating an established mobile brand in the events space. To do that we understand that it will take organic growth. To build this growth we have to work with communities across the country to establish NABR as a platform for local events. In addition, we have to support that growth with a great product.  We want NABR to be a product that continues to get better with what our customers want. And the best way for us to do that is to focus on what we have done well so far: listen to the customer. We listen, plan and push the enhancements that we see our customers want and are strategic to our long-term growth.',NULL,25,'2013-10-25 02:51:47','2013-10-25 02:51:47',9),(171,0,'May 2013',NULL,25,'2013-10-25 02:51:52','2013-10-25 02:51:52',10),(172,0,'July 2013',NULL,25,'2013-10-25 02:51:54','2013-10-25 02:51:54',11),(173,0,'Yes',NULL,25,'2013-10-25 02:51:56','2013-10-25 02:51:56',12),(174,0,'Yes',NULL,25,'2013-10-25 02:51:58','2013-10-25 02:51:58',13),(175,0,'25',NULL,25,'2013-10-25 02:52:00','2013-10-25 02:52:00',14),(176,1,'200 Hours',NULL,25,'2013-10-25 02:52:02','2013-10-25 02:52:17',16),(177,2,'5000',NULL,25,'2013-10-25 02:52:03','2013-10-25 02:52:42',15),(178,0,'0',NULL,25,'2013-10-25 02:52:46','2013-10-25 02:52:46',20),(179,0,'1',NULL,25,'2013-10-25 02:52:50','2013-10-25 02:52:50',17),(180,0,'2',NULL,25,'2013-10-25 02:52:51','2013-10-25 02:52:51',18),(181,2,'As a group of transplants to a new city, we individually saw a problem with trying to find events. We came together to create a great product that will solve this problem. As a team, we have complemented each other\'s skill sets to build our Android MVP, as we continue; we have realize that we have the talent and skills  to bring a product to market. Now we need help in fulfilling that idea and scaling it to build a great company and a great product. ',NULL,25,'2013-10-25 02:56:30','2013-10-25 02:58:20',21),(182,0,'klnionoin',NULL,29,'2013-10-26 15:00:54','2013-10-26 15:00:54',2),(183,0,'jknkjbjb',NULL,29,'2013-10-26 15:00:57','2013-10-26 15:00:57',3),(184,0,'kjbhuihuihi',NULL,29,'2013-10-26 15:01:01','2013-10-26 15:01:01',4),(185,0,'No',NULL,29,'2013-10-26 15:01:02','2013-10-26 15:01:02',5),(186,0,'hvjh',NULL,29,'2013-10-26 15:01:07','2013-10-26 15:01:07',6),(187,1,'Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit, sed diam nonummy nibh euismod tincidunt ut laoreet dolore magna aliquam erat volutpat. Ut wisi enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exerci tation ullamcorper suscipit lobortis nisl ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis autem vel eum iriure dolor in hendrerit in vulputate velit esse molestie consequat, vel illum dolore eu feugiat nulla facilisis at vero eros et accumsan et iusto odio dignissim qui blandit praesent luptatum zzril delenit augue duis dolore te feugait nulla facilisi. Nam liber tempor cum soluta nobis eleifend option congue nihil imperdiet doming id quod mazim placerat facer possim assum. Typi non habent claritatem insitam; est usus legentis in iis qui facit eorum claritatem. Investigationes demonstraverunt lectores legere me lius quod ii legunt saepius. Claritas est etiam processus dynamicus, qui sequitur mutationem consuetudium lectorum. Mirum est notare quam littera gothica, quam nunc putamus parum claram, antepo',NULL,31,'2013-10-27 06:35:03','2013-10-27 06:41:42',2),(188,1,'Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit, sed diam nonummy nibh euismod tincidunt ut laoreet dolore magna aliquam erat volutpat. Ut wisi enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exerci tation ullamcorper suscipit lobortis nisl ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis autem vel eum iriure dolor in hendrerit in vulputate ve