r of vehicle on roads on weekdays which in turn solve traffic on roads.',NULL,52,'2013-10-31 15:48:40','2013-10-31 15:50:20',4),(257,0,'Yes',NULL,52,'2013-10-31 15:50:21','2013-10-31 15:50:21',5),(258,0,'Through Events, Taxi Companies and IT companies',NULL,52,'2013-10-31 15:50:45','2013-10-31 15:50:45',6),(259,0,'Connecting people locally for daily commute to reduce traffic on roads.\nTo reduce traffic on roads, we are working to number of vehicle on roads on weekdays.',NULL,52,'2013-10-31 15:51:38','2013-10-31 15:51:38',1),(260,0,'Expertise in Technology front.\nTechnical Team\nCan not outsource because no investors',NULL,52,'2013-10-31 15:53:07','2013-10-31 15:53:07',7),(261,0,'We are taking help from friends & family.',NULL,52,'2013-10-31 15:53:25','2013-10-31 15:53:25',8),(262,0,'1.5 years back ',NULL,52,'2013-10-31 15:53:45','2013-10-31 15:53:45',10),(263,0,'When i cam from Mumbai to Pune and saw that pune also gain shape like mumbai in terms of traffic.',NULL,52,'2013-10-31 15:54:39','2013-10-31 15:54:39',11),(264,0,'Currently we are focusing on user base with every user should provide daily commute details .\nAnalyse the data. and come up with model which really solve human pain points ( traffic when they daily commute).\n  ',NULL,52,'2013-10-31 15:56:29','2013-10-31 15:56:29',9),(265,0,'Yes',NULL,52,'2013-10-31 15:56:35','2013-10-31 15:56:35',12),(266,0,'No',NULL,52,'2013-10-31 15:56:48','2013-10-31 15:56:48',13),(267,0,'We have version 1 ready. We need help for version 2.',NULL,52,'2013-10-31 15:57:21','2013-10-31 15:57:21',16),(268,0,'NA',NULL,52,'2013-10-31 15:58:02','2013-10-31 15:58:02',15),(269,0,'0',NULL,52,'2013-10-31 15:58:11','2013-10-31 15:58:11',20),(270,0,'0',NULL,52,'2013-10-31 15:58:31','2013-10-31 15:58:31',18),(271,1,'I love hitching and want to change the perception about hitching  in India.',NULL,52,'2013-10-31 15:59:28','2013-10-31 16:00:07',21),(272,1,'2',NULL,53,'2013-11-01 20:08:57','2013-11-02 02:05:43',17),(273,1,'Yes',NULL,53,'2013-11-01 20:10:00','2013-11-03 04:22:24',5),(274,2,'Amazi is a location-based app that makes it easy to find water from filters, fountains and faucets to fill reusable bottles. We also provide data on the municipal water quality so users can make informed decisions regarding their water. Our goal is to eliminate the need for bottled water by making filling reusable bottles as easy as buying a new one.',NULL,53,'2013-11-01 20:10:51','2013-11-03 20:34:35',1),(275,9,'We had previously founded Amplofi, a socially conscious startup in the music industry, before putting that on hold to address the dire environmental needs of our planet. \n\nThe concept for Amazi was born during a heatwave last summer while out of town for a music festival. Only after extensively searching online for somewhere to fill our water jugs did we realize that not only was no one providing this service, but there were a ton of people out there (like us) posting questions about where to find clean water sources to refill their containers.\n\nAfter presenting the idea at a local Startup Weekend, we were encouraged by the response. In addition to winning over the judges, we were also able to validate the market potentialboth from a business and consumer standpointand earn the respect of our peers. \n\nWe\'ve since been awarded with \"Most Promising Emerging Business\" from the Think Beyond Plastic global innovation competition and have every intention of living up to that title.',NULL,53,'2013-11-01 20:10:53','2013-11-04 03:58:08',2),(276,3,'Amazi is the only app of its kind that provides nationwide locations of filtered water dispensers, drinking fountains and springs, while also supplying information on the municipal water qualityboth of which have proven essential in swaying the public from bottled water. Since many of our competitors are non-profits working on opensource projects, our multiple revenue channels, proprietary data and strategic partnerships will allow us to quickly become industry leaders.',NULL,53,'2013-11-01 20:10:55','2013-11-02 04:35:23',3),(277,3,'Of the 66 billion plastic water bottles consumed annually in the United States, only 13% of them are recycled. More than 90% of Americans own reusable bottles, yet the accessibility of bottled water and the uncertainty regarding municipal water quality allow it to prevail. Dozens of cities, hundreds of campuses, and even more businesses and retailers have installed water refill stations and even banned the sale of bottled water, yet there\'s currently no effective way to find these locations.',NULL,53,'2013-11-01 20:10:58','2013-11-03 04:22:24',4),(278,2,'1) Dev support\n2) Fundraising\n3) Data acquisition',NULL,53,'2013-11-01 20:11:59','2013-11-03 22:48:45',7),(279,5,'1) Looking for tech co-founder; Securing funding to hire dev team; Winning 500Hrs :)\n2) Impact investors; Crowdfunding; Incubators; Grants\n3) Contact filtered water dispenser/water fountain companies (locations); Datamining (locations/water quality); OpenStreetMap (locations); Crowdsourcing (locations/water quality), Government agencies (water quality), Affiliate marketing networks (deals)',NULL,53,'2013-11-01 20:16:38','2013-11-03 23:58:29',8),(280,1,'July 2012',NULL,53,'2013-11-01 20:16:58','2013-11-03 22:45:22',10),(281,0,'January 2013',NULL,53,'2013-11-01 20:17:07','2013-11-01 20:17:07',11),(282,1,'[3 mo] Test/validate MVP in select cities; Finalize business plan/financial projections; Launch marketing website; Expand advisory board\n\n[6 mo] Public beta release (iOS); Launch web app (RWD); Initiate pilot programs with retailers (refine business model/conversion funnel); Acquire seed funding ($100k); First hires (dev/sales/interns); Build and deploy street teams (evangelists/change makers); Acquire filtered water dispensers; Partner with reusable bottle manufacturers; Attend festivals/events/conferences (dispense water/sell bottles)\n\n[12 mo] Product refinement/expansion (iOS): deals, check-ins, user profiles, reviews; PR/marketing push; Launch online marketplace (revenue generation); Refine growth engine; Series A ($1M); \n\n[18 mo] Product refinement/expansion (iOS): social integration, retention programs (Track Your Impact); Launch Android app; Develop API (data licensing); Form key partnerships (filtration systems/reusable bottles/fitness apps); Optimize conversion funnel/sales process\n\n[24 mo] Increase advertising and sales efforts; Optimize customer acquisition strategies; Series B ($3M); Hire executive staff; Amazi-branded water machines in high-traffic retail locations (Starbucks, Chipotle, 7-Eleven)\n\n[36 mo]  Expand into international markets; Position company for strategic merger/acquisition; Product R&D (filtered systems/bottles/mobile test kit); Establish separate 501(c)(3) entity\n',NULL,53,'2013-11-01 20:23:47','2013-11-02 02:02:02',9),(283,0,'0',NULL,55,'2013-11-01 23:00:22','2013-11-01 23:00:22',17),(284,0,'Yes',NULL,53,'2013-11-02 02:02:14','2013-11-02 02:02:14',12),(285,0,'No',NULL,53,'2013-11-02 02:02:20','2013-11-02 02:02:20',13),(286,0,'$5000',NULL,53,'2013-11-02 02:03:06','2013-11-02 02:03:06',15),(287,1,'200-300, if we\'re talking about testing core assumptions.',NULL,53,'2013-11-02 02:05:20','2013-11-03 23:34:15',16),(288,1,'1',NULL,53,'2013-11-02 02:05:25','2013-11-02 02:05:31',20),(289,0,'2',NULL,53,'2013-11-02 02:05:54','2013-11-02 02:05:54',18),(290,0,'https://speakerdeck.com/dlyttle/amazi-pitch-deck',NULL,53,'2013-11-02 02:06:19','2013-11-02 02:06:19',19),(291,2,'As responsible stewards of the Earth, we are constantly looking for ways to better our surroundings and give back to our global community. As social entrepreneurs, we are passionate about creating elegantly simple solutions to complex environmental and humanitarian issues. Amazi is the harmonious balance between those two worlds and serves as the catalyst for creating significant and lasting change.\n',NULL,53,'2013-11-02 02:06:22','2013-11-04 03:59:01',21),(292,0,'In addition to our early adopters who have signed up, users (consumers) are acquired through grassroots marketing initiatives, targeted advertising, industry blogs, and enlisting evangelists to spread the word. Our initial customer segment (businesses with water dispensers)consisting of grocery stores, coffee shops and cafsare acquired through targeted advertising, PR and third party affiliates, such as coupon services and reward programs, with existing clients in our target markets.',NULL,53,'2013-11-02 04:10:49','2013-11-02 04:10:49',6),(293,1,'',NULL,53,'2013-11-03 23:32:44','2013-11-07 09:57:12',14),(294,1,'1',NULL,59,'2013-11-06 21:23:44','2013-11-19 03:15:37',17),(295,1,'1',NULL,60,'2013-11-06 23:52:38','2013-11-09 23:31:04',17),(296,0,'\nIntroducing BoomCeleb.com, the first ever social website that lets Fans earn points to win prizes and memorabilia from their favorite or any Celebrity around the world for free. BoomCeleb is designed for Celebrities of all kinds including athletes, musicians, politicians, movie stars, Hollywood personalities, and local, national, or global famous persons. BoomCeleb\'s modern social technology generates ad-based revenue.',NULL,60,'2013-11-06 23:53:42','2013-11-06 23:53:42',1),(297,0,'Nothing like this exists in the social, digital marketplace now. This is a very special, unique opportunity. We think of a sports\nCelebrity like next year\'s Superbowl or FIFA World Cup in 2014 Brazil. A special Celebrity offering unique memorabilia that\'s one\nof a kind (shirt, cleats used in game, etc.)',NULL,60,'2013-11-07 00:06:23','2013-11-07 00:06:23',3),(298,1,'Celebrities love their Fans\' attention; can it be monetized? Fans love their Celebrities (Lady Gaga, Justin Bieber,etc.) and would love a chance to win memorabilia without paying a fortune. Advertisers would love to sell digital\nadvertisements to the right audience at the right time in the right channel. All three customers have demands. How can Fans get a chance? How can Celebrities earn from their online presence? How can Advertising tap-in to this\ngolden network?',NULL,60,'2013-11-07 00:08:19','2013-11-07 00:08:42',4),(299,0,'Yes',NULL,60,'2013-11-07 00:09:10','2013-11-07 00:09:10',5),(300,0,'Fans: Want to earn memorabilia from your favorite Celebrity? Choose your favorate Celebrity\'s contest to win.\nCelebrities: Easily reach out to your adoring fans. Earn more in 30 minutes than a whole tv series or weekend show.\nAdvertisers: Finally a great solution for targeting online advertisements with active audience participation.',NULL,60,'2013-11-07 00:13:53','2013-11-07 00:13:53',6),(301,1,'Stanley Fredericq, CEO of BoomCeleb, born and raised in Haiti. i am an innovative entrepreneur who comes up with ideas that people can use practically. An entrepreneur searches for change, responds to it and exploits opportunities. I am a forward thinker and would love to give back to the world.',NULL,60,'2013-11-07 00:22:09','2013-11-07 00:22:40',2),(302,0,'0',NULL,61,'2013-11-07 23:35:59','2013-11-07 23:35:59',17),(303,0,'Dev, web designer and finance',NULL,60,'2013-11-09 23:26:10','2013-11-09 23:26:10',7),(304,0,'The BoomCeleb.com solution makes these loves a reality. This solution does not exist anywhere. We provide web-based social contests for Celebrities to offer their personal items to Fans that earned points by participating in online Advertisements. Fans can view Advertisements and earn a chance in an exclusive contest. Celebrities can run multiple contests. In each contest BoomCeleb.com would share the profits with the celebrity. Advertisers can see results of their placements. Each contest etc.',NULL,60,'2013-11-09 23:26:42','2013-11-09 23:26:42',8),(305,0,'Year 1 impact includes initial customer build-up in each area. Celebrity Lady Gaga has 20M +Twitter followers so each contest will reach 5 millions fans. We offer subprime advertising PPC 20 cents with each advertisement earning 1 point per fan when viewed. Revenue estimated $2M. Year 3 impact includes a portfolio of Celebrities, each with multiple contests. The Fan base grows globally at a rate proportional to Celebrity impact, estimated at 500 million fans. Revenue estimated to earn $200M.',NULL,60,'2013-11-09 23:28:11','2013-11-09 23:28:11',9),(306,0,'November 2011',NULL,60,'2013-11-09 23:28:31','2013-11-09 23:28:31',10),(307,0,'January 2011',NULL,60,'2013-11-09 23:28:41','2013-11-09 23:28:41',11),(308,0,'Yes',NULL,60,'2013-11-09 23:29:26','2013-11-09 23:29:26',12),(309,0,'Yes',NULL,60,'2013-11-09 23:29:32','2013-11-09 23:29:32',13),(310,0,'$ 200',NULL,60,'2013-11-09 23:30:00','2013-11-09 23:30:00',14),(311,0,'I don\'t know',NULL,60,'2013-11-09 23:30:18','2013-11-09 23:30:18',16),(312,0,'$5000',NULL,60,'2013-11-09 23:30:41','2013-11-09 23:30:41',15),(313,0,'0',NULL,60,'2013-11-09 23:30:54','2013-11-09 23:30:54',20),(314,0,'1',NULL,60,'2013-11-09 23:31:11','2013-11-09 23:31:11',18),(315,0,'Because I would love to give back to the world and this startup the mission behind it is to give back to the world.\nBoomCeleb.com is a huge win-win-win solution to the overall problem of monetizing the social connections with Fans, Celebrities, and Advertisers. There is a tremendous amount of revenue to generate.',NULL,60,'2013-11-09 23:33:27','2013-11-09 23:33:27',21),(316,1,'3',NULL,63,'2013-11-11 07:17:04','2013-11-14 08:24:40',17),(317,0,'Yes',NULL,37,'2013-11-12 03:14:13','2013-11-12 03:14:13',5),(318,0,'0',NULL,20,'2013-11-12 13:55:54','2013-11-12 13:55:54',17),(319,0,'TWS is a job recommendation engine that will present users with relevant job opportunities for them (StubleUpon for jobs). At the first stage we ask our users to filter their desired fields of occupation, then the system will prompt the user with one job post at a time. As the user uses our product the system will learn and analyze their engagement- similar to what Outbrain is doing with content. This is a two stage process- at first using mobile devices, then on a work station. \n',NULL,59,'2013-11-13 18:54:34','2013-11-13 18:54:34',1),(320,1,'The idea of a job recommendation engine came to us as one of our founders has been looking for a job for a few months. He was deeply frustrated by the process of the job search, it was cold, the layout of the job boards are out of date and generally, we don\'t consume content in the same fasion anymore. \nWe thought about all the time spent looking for a job as well as the available products we are familiar with today for content discovery and thought about combining the two together- content recommendation and job searching. Furthermore, introducing users to a new innovative layout we believe that will increase retention to out product. \n\nThe way we see it, by building an engine that learns the users\' engagement and behavior we can later recommend and deliver relevant posts to them. But the innovation doesn\'t stop there, the UI is a key player in our product. We want to take the job search industry two steps forward using available technology and popular UI. ',NULL,59,'2013-11-13 18:57:54','2013-11-13 19:09:11',2),(321,0,'In order to acquire users we will answer the question: \"Which industry makes most hires through the internet?\". We will then know what type of users are hired for those jobs, basically we will find our target segment. Using influencers and industry leaders we will market our product to that segment for proof of concept. \nWe will want to creat several success stories in that industry gaining brand recognition before expanding to the next industry. That will be the scale cycle of TWS.\n',NULL,59,'2013-11-13 18:57:57','2013-11-13 18:57:57',6),(322,0,'Yes',NULL,59,'2013-11-13 18:57:57','2013-11-13 18:57:57',5),(323,0,'I love crowdfunding & have funded nearly 30 projects on Kickstarter. I\'ve seen pain & frustration from both creators & backers when issues occur that cause delays or mistakes. I\'m in a unique position to be able to help solve this problem (for certain types of projects) with my experience in the printing industry. The commercial printing industry is in decline and I see this as a opportunity to use my experience to do something really cool and help artist earn income doing what they love to do.',NULL,13,'2013-11-13 23:04:05','2013-11-13 23:04:05',21),(324,0,'https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/47775644/CI%20Pitch%20INCOMPLETE.pdf',NULL,13,'2013-11-13 23:04:14','2013-11-13 23:04:14',19),(325,0,'0',NULL,64,'2013-11-14 02:48:22','2013-11-14 02:48:22',17),(326,1,'Our team came together first as friends and now as partners. Danny, who is a Elite Yelp user, was dissatisfied with elements of the Yelp platform and found that friends constantly asked him for date and restaurant recommendations. We brainstormed and decided that a mobile product which simplified the process of planning a date would add a lot of value to peoples lives. ',NULL,63,'2013-11-14 07:57:38','2013-11-15 10:08:24',2),(327,2,'Most solutions, such as Yelp, aggregate information / opinions for the general public. The user is left to sift through the information. Two Sense will tailor recommendations specifically to users, based on our algorithm, the users preferences, and thus filter out the overload of unneeded Information. Our premium plan will allow users to plan and book their entire evening (including cars, flowers, concerts) through Two Sense. In the future we will plan nights out for groups, families and more. ',NULL,63,'2013-11-14 07:58:08','2013-11-15 10:11:32',3),(328,2,'Yes',NULL,63,'2013-11-14 07:58:09','2013-11-14 07:58:14',5),(329,2,'We have already begun recruiting potential users on both the business and the booking side. On the business side we are in discussions with  potential partners (restaurants & dating websites) that want 1.) exposure and / or 2.) the potential to entice users who are planning a date. On the user side, we have already started collecting email addresses of interested individuals. We look to total 500 - 1,000 plus before our initial launch. ',NULL,63,'2013-11-14 07:59:01','2013-11-15 10:12:41',6),(330,2,'A one stop platform that provides personalized date recommendations. Our platform eliminates the stress of choice and creates a unique solution that is curated by the users location, taste and the nature of the occasion.',NULL,63,'2013-11-14 08:00:33','2013-11-19 23:57:41',1),(331,2,'Planning a date is hard! We want to make it fun and easy by giving you a killer date idea. Two Sense simplifies life. Youre on the beach but have a date across town in 2 hours and havent planned anything? We create the date so you can focus on enjoying it. We translate wants and ideas into tangible options. The number of parties, anniversary dinners, business dinners or 1st dates planned every day are countless. We want to eliminate the stress of choice and ensure the best night possible.',NULL,63,'2013-11-14 08:08:32','2013-11-15 10:14:48',4),(332,4,'Year 1: Build a user base and really hone in on our algorithm in LA for year 1. For the latter half of year the focus will be on the introduction of the premium service.\nYear 2: Expand the service to SF and NYC with the basic service and code the algorithm accordingly.\nYear 3: Introduce the premium service for all 3 cities.  Major back end partnerships across the board. Goal is to have 2 million users using our service by year 3. We look to for about 10% of our user base to become premium users subscribing for $5 monthly to enjoy full booking capabilities. ',NULL,63,'2013-11-14 08:11:28','2013-11-19 23:47:56',9),(333,1,'The initial problem was identified about 10 months ago. We came up with the idea about two months ago.',NULL,63,'2013-11-14 08:12:10','2013-11-15 10:16:09',10),(334,1,'2 months ago. ',NULL,63,'2013-11-14 08:12:45','2013-11-15 10:16:25',11),(335,0,'1. Development Team or CTO\n2. Funding \n3. Personalized Algorithm ',NULL,63,'2013-11-14 08:13:15','2013-11-14 08:13:15',7),(336,2,'1.)     We are exploring other options besides 500 Hours/Cause code to get the best possible solution and bring us to market quickly. We have two potential CTO\'s lined up who could manage or develop the product, whether or not we are accepted Into 500 hours. We have also reached out to some developers, both overseas and in the US,  who we have worked with in the past and are interested in helping us develop an MVP.\n2.)      We are in conversation with a few investors who are excited by the elevator pitch and the wireframes we showed them. We are keeping a dialogue open with these investors while also pursuing accelerator / incubator opportunities.\n3.)      We are speaking with experienced developers who are helping us hone in on the best approach for building the algorithm across platforms. We have compiled a lengthy list of LA-based restaurants and institutions that can be mapped to the algorithm and will form the basis of the initial recommendation system. ',NULL,63,'2013-11-14 08:17:59','2013-11-15 10:15:31',8),(337,0,'Yes',NULL,63,'2013-11-14 08:23:37','2013-11-14 08:23:37',12),(338,0,'Yes',NULL,63,'2013-11-14 08:23:44','2013-11-14 08:23:44',13),(339,0,'$50',NULL,63,'2013-11-14 08:23:51','2013-11-14 08:23:51',14),(340,0,'200-250 Hours ',NULL,63,'2013-11-14 08:24:07','2013-11-14 08:24:07',16),(341,0,'$15000',NULL,63,'2013-11-14 08:24:30','2013-11-14 08:24:30',15),(342,0,'0',NULL,63,'2013-11-14 08:24:34','2013-11-14 08:24:34',20),(343,0,'3',NULL,63,'2013-11-14 08:24:45','2013-11-14 08:24:45',18),(344,2,'We have a passion for it and believe it can do become a very profitable business that really adds value to people\'s live. Our initial testing of the idea and the feedback we have received from potential customers has only buttressed our belief. \n\nWe\'ve been able to make large strides offline and now think we can bring it online to realize our vision and make an efficient, useful, and profitable company.',NULL,63,'2013-11-14 08:25:16','2013-11-19 23:56:30',21),(345,0,'0',NULL,68,'2013-11-15 13:35:07','2013-11-15 13:35:07',17),(346,0,'0',NULL,69,'2013-11-15 14:27:01','2013-11-15 14:27:01',17),(347,1,'0.  We are all full time students but we designate about 20 hours a week to Render.',NULL,41,'2013-11-16 02:32:29','2013-11-28 02:06:27',17),(348,0,' I was born the youngest son of a single mother in Kingston Jamaica. My Mother and family moved to the United states when i was still young for a better opportunities. Growing up in america society i witness all the possible things i be, but when i was in high school i developed a love for technology, and how it was constantly changing.  After i graduated and my first attempt at college didn\'t go the way i taught, i joined the Air force for a chance to improve my career option. Unfortunately my service time was cut short from physical issues that developed.  When returning home took a second chance at College and now i am a semester away from receiving my Bachelors in Information science and technology.  I choose this degree because of my passion and love for how technology can be so different and be developed by so many different and diverse people. ',NULL,11,'2013-11-17 11:46:25','2013-11-17 11:46:25',2),(349,0,'The concept behind this idea is not a new idea, but a pivot and different vision of a already existing trend that is already established. We are using this vision in hope to bring the Internet Informative sites (Wikipedia, etc), Social application, and Media(Music, videos, etc) all in a way that maximizes the users experience. \n\nThis concept will also lead into a new form of analytic studying, because it will take the users input which is constantly changing.',NULL,11,'2013-11-17 11:53:16','2013-11-17 11:53:16',3),(350,0,'The impact we are trying to make is finding the answer to a question we asked our self.  That is \"How can hash-tag be more useful, and what can we do with the metadata embed in everything?\". ',NULL,11,'2013-11-17 11:59:13','2013-11-17 11:59:13',4),(351,0,'1. Finding talented and committed developers.\n2. Building a strong team, with mentors and more.\n3. Developing the way we want this product to be used.',NULL,11,'2013-11-17 12:03:26','2013-11-17 12:03:26',7),(352,0,'With the help of entrepreneur advisor in my local area, i was able to be introduce to mentors with experience of developing business model. These mentors have help guide me and taught me how to use the Business model canvas to help with my process. While these mentors have also tried to help me find and build a team of strong developers from the local area or out of state, i have not had any luck and slowly beginning looking through other channels such as contractors or building the application my self. ',NULL,11,'2013-11-17 12:06:54','2013-11-17 12:06:54',8),(353,1,' 2010, while i was watching movies and Simultaneously searching the internet for information about the movie.',NULL,11,'2013-11-17 12:07:55','2013-11-17 12:08:09',10),(354,0,'After coming home from the military and going back to college. ',NULL,11,'2013-11-17 12:09:21','2013-11-17 12:09:21',11),(355,0,'For the next 3 years, i want to focus on developing a minimal viable product, for beta testing by End-user and to see what we can do to improve on the technology both for the user and business as well. ',NULL,11,'2013-11-17 12:13:35','2013-11-17 12:13:35',9),(356,0,'Yes',NULL,11,'2013-11-17 12:13:42','2013-11-17 12:13:42',13),(357,0,'50$',NULL,11,'2013-11-17 12:13:52','2013-11-17 12:13:52',14),(358,0,'400',NULL,11,'2013-11-17 12:14:04','2013-11-17 12:14:04',16),(359,0,'4000',NULL,11,'2013-11-17 12:14:20','2013-11-17 12:14:20',15),(360,1,'1',NULL,11,'2013-11-17 12:14:24','2013-11-17 12:14:27',20),(361,0,'1',NULL,11,'2013-11-17 12:14:38','2013-11-17 12:14:38',18),(362,1,'I want to do this startup, because i think it is the next step in how users will receive data and information from all the content on the internet. ',NULL,11,'2013-11-17 12:15:13','2013-11-17 12:15:45',21),(363,0,'https://drive.google.com/file/d/0BxLCSW56ZvfRNU9kcml3b3VveDg/edit?usp=sharing',NULL,11,'2013-11-17 12:17:21','2013-11-17 12:17:21',19),(364,0,'The job searching industry is old fashioned and does not allow users to recieve the maximum for their searching efforts. Many companies focus on analyzing your CV, great but what about behavior? We are building a product that learns users\' behavior and makes recommendations based on that. Based on what REALLY interests them. We are also introducing a new form of browsing opportunities. The whole system is designed in a sophisticated form that alighns user content consumption (mobile then comp.).',NULL,59,'2013-11-17 20:47:36','2013-11-17 20:47:36',3),(365,0,'We are going to deliver to job seekers the most refined and personel job recommendations for them. We are taking \"head hunters\" to the mass inteding to distrupt the industry. No longer will head hunting be for high end careers rather for the masses. Learning our users\' engagement, we will be able to make the best recommendations for them. Doing so we will be able to make great fits both for employers both for employees hence reducing employee churn rate and saving companies time and money. ',NULL,59,'2013-11-17 20:56:06','2013-11-17 20:56:06',4),(366,0,'1. Building a sophisticated and smart product- our team does not have domain expertise in building algorithms despite having techies in the team. We will have to learn how to develop smart quality algorithms.\n2. Correct positioning and growth- we\'ll have to find the exact industries where we can create the most success stories.\n3. Attracting talent- always a challenge in early stage ventures.',NULL,59,'2013-11-17 21:24:55','2013-11-17 21:24:55',7),(367,4,'1. In order to correctly build smart sophisticated algorithms we will have to have guidance by experts. We are in search of a smart advisory board. The advisory board will help us gain expertise and steadiness. It will help us draw talent and investors as those will see the opportunity in the new venture we are creating. The second stage will be hiring industry experts that will be part of the team building those algorithms. We see this as an opportunity for those engineers to join a new company where they can shine and influence the decision making.\n2. In order for our company to succeed we need to give our users real value. No one will use our product if it doesn\'t improve their search and process. Hence, we have to find the most relevant industries to launch in. This means that we will answer such questions as \"What industry makes most hires off the internet?\", \"Where are most hires made off the internet?\". The goal will be to create success stories then expand to other industries and locations.\n3. Every venture has hiring difficulties at its start. I recently heard \"The harder the problem, the easier to recruit talent\". We really relate to this and believe that once we have a clear, solid strategy, proof of concept, strong advisory and investor interest it will be easy to make those hires. Of course it\'s a long way but we have a large local network and can allow top talent to shine with large responsibility and a chance to determinate processes. This will be stage 2.\n',NULL,59,'2013-11-17 21:24:57','2013-11-19 03:13:54',8),(368,0,'$50',NULL,33,'2013-11-18 08:58:22','2013-11-18 08:58:22',14),(369,1,'1',NULL,70,'2013-11-18 19:11:00','2013-11-18 21:36:47',17),(370,1,'Consumers struggle to use gift cards to get meaningful gifts and often the cards go unused. Retailers want people to use the cards more often. Why? Because, on average, consumers spend ~17% more than the card balance when making purchases. Likewise, consumers convert at a much higher rate online when offers and coupons are available. Combining offers with gift cards give the consumers and the retailers more value in a much more likely transaction. Revenue is generated from commissions on sales.',NULL,70,'2013-11-18 19:14:51','2013-11-18 21:39:04',1),(371,2,'Kevin Strawbridge and Adam Smith have over 25 years of experience in, and around eCommerce and online marketing. Both have successfully led online deal/coupon sites. In the case of Kevin, he was appointed as president of DealTaker.com and grew this division of Media General, Inc. into a top 15 deals/coupons website (according to comScore) achieving over 24 million site visits in 2011 producing over $10MM in commission revenue off of $145MM in referred revenue to merchant partners. \n\nAt the same time, Adam started and ran a unique cash back and member network in the deals/coupons space called Blastoff Network. The concept was validated through its successful venture funding and strategic partnerships with major companies.\n\nAdam and Kevin seek a unique, new way to attract and retain online shoppers and provide all involved (consumer, retailer, deal platform) with a strong value proposition. CardSpur is based on combining shoppers with purchase intent and available money to spend.',NULL,70,'2013-11-18 19:19:09','2013-11-18 21:39:59',2),(372,0,'CardSpur isn\'t completely unique in that there are many deal/coupon sites. What is unique is creating value for the consumers and the retailers at the intersection of purchase intent and available funds. Typical deal/coupon sites are for regular shoppers spending cash. CardSpur adds value to available funds to spend and helps to complete redemption of the loaded funds. For example, if one has a Nordstrom gift card with $100 in value and it is combined with a 20% discount it adds $25 in value.',NULL,70,'2013-11-18 19:31:24','2013-11-18 19:31:24',3),(373,0,'The impact of CardSpur is two-sided. Consumers often leave gift cards unused due to oversight or not being motivated to use the cards. Redeeming the cards for them unlocks the value and fulfills the intent of gift-giving. Retailers need gift cards to be redeemed. Unused gift cards are a liability to retailers. Redemption moves the value of the card from a liability to revenue (and often above the value of the original card purchase). Combining these outcomes creates economic stimulus.',NULL,70,'2013-11-18 19:35:36','2013-11-18 19:35:36',4),(374,0,'No',NULL,70,'2013-11-18 19:35:36','2013-11-18 19:35:36',5),(375,0,'Attracting a retaining consumers will be done through a multitude of marketing means. Online options will include display advertising, SEO/PPC, and social methods. Hybrid options will include PR and word of mouth activities. Offline will utilize partnerships with retailers and companies that are in contact with gift card purchasers at the point of sale. Over the long-term, users will be retained through activation as registered users and active involvement in the community aspect of the business',NULL,70,'2013-11-18 19:39:46','2013-11-18 19:39:46',6),(376,0,'1. Creating a solid, sustainable technology interface. This includes consumer facing as well as back-end management.\n2. Creating retailer relationships with companies that traditionally do not work with discount sites (e.g. Ralph Lauren, Victoria\'s Secret, Neiman Marcus, others).\n3. Generating interest for consumers and retailers.',NULL,70,'2013-11-18 19:44:27','2013-11-18 19:44:27',7),(377,2,'1. To get to a sold and sustainable technology interface, we plan to find a top developer/designer with a passion for online marketing and eCommerce. We want someone who understands user experience, product/info feed development, and clean/elegant coding. Likewise, content management and smart work processes will be needed. Over time, this will build out to a team of people focused on a longer-term road map.\n\n2. Based on relationships between Kevin and Adam, we will first identify as many retailers as possible that we can immediately set-up and get running with little obstruction. Early on we will identify our list of \"nice to have\" retailer that may be resistant and begin cultivating the value proposition for the retailer - namely that it is not a price issue as much as it is a redemption issue and that we can help that. Where we cannot directly start those conversations, we will rely on our very vast network to get introductions and create the discussions.\n\n3. As stated previously, we plan to create buzz around creating free value in gift cards. It never fails when we talk about this business with people that gift cards are often overlooked. It is essentially cash in one\'s pocket. When we make that cash worth more by doing nothing other than going to a site that will calculate the value of offers, we will hook people. Everyone is looking for deals these days - CardSpur will not only provide the deals, but unlock the money they have available in the cards.',NULL,70,'2013-11-18 19:59:19','2013-11-18 21:43:20',8),(378,1,'The first six months will be all about the look and feel of the website and the \"plumbing\" behind how to pair the offers with the cards. It will also be about establishing affiliate relationships with retailers to build revenue.\n\nOnce the base of the website is established, the focus will turn over the next year to creating the best possible access points for information. This will pinpoint mobile opportunities - specifically how to store offers for use within stores.\n\nWith the mobile platform in place, the next half year will drive the cross platform integration to create seamless options for storing card and deal information and using it wherever the consumer would like.\n\nFinally, year three will be about optimizing digital tools to minimize the reliance on physical cards and redemption of offers.\n\nThroughout this period of time, other areas will have constant refinement and upgrades. These include - \n\n1. Content management - creating easy ways to get information into and out of the systems to make it \"Fisher Price\" simple for users\n\n2. Marketing systems - Utilizing external and internal marketing tools in order help consumers and retailers enjoy the benefits of redeemed gift cards.\n\n3. Administration - making it easy (and as automated as possible) on the associates of CardSpur so that more time is available for long-term innovation.',NULL,70,'2013-11-18 21:34:12','2013-11-18 21:43:53',9),(379,0,'Late 2011 - got hung up in too many big ideas and lost focus',NULL,70,'2013-11-18 21:35:01','2013-11-18 21:35:01',10),(380,0,'October 2013 - By focusing down to the intersection of deals and cards',NULL,70,'2013-11-18 21:35:15','2013-11-18 21:35:15',11),(381,0,'Yes',NULL,70,'2013-11-18 21:35:25','2013-11-18 21:35:25',12),(382,0,'Yes',NULL,70,'2013-11-18 21:35:26','2013-11-18 21:35:26',13),(383,0,'100',NULL,70,'2013-11-18 21:35:28','2013-11-18 21:35:28',14),(384,0,'350',NULL,70,'2013-11-18 21:35:33','2013-11-18 21:35:33',16),(385,0,'25000',NULL,70,'2013-11-18 21:35:40','2013-11-18 21:35:40',15),(386,0,'Kevin is passionate about the deal/coupon space. Having also been on the retail side (JCPenney.com) he recognizes that deal/coupon offers are looked at very narrowly. By adding value to both sides of the equation, he sees a way to really distinguish a new model. Adam has started and successfully exited other businesses. He sees an opportunity to continue his path while also using his skills in a well-suited way. Both partners are excited to create another successful business in the Dallas area.',NULL,70,'2013-11-18 21:36:07','2013-11-18 21:36:07',21),(387,0,'2',NULL,70,'2013-11-18 21:36:10','2013-11-18 21:36:10',18),(388,0,'0',NULL,70,'2013-11-18 21:36:51','2013-11-18 21:36:51',20),(389,1,'testtesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttest',NULL,20,'2013-11-18 23:40:28','2013-11-18 23:40:54',2),(390,1,'testtesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttest',NULL,20,'2013-11-18 23:40:29','2013-11-18 23:40:57',3),(391,1,'testtesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttesttest',NULL,20,'2013-11-18 23:4