After validating the concept with a dozen people that are smarter than we are combined. ',NULL,59,'2013-11-19 02:21:58','2013-11-19 02:21:58',11),(407,0,'Months 1-3: Validation and pain refining. These months are dedicated to understanding the problem we want to solve. It\'s about understanding the market, the competitors and discovering the users. This stage is super important as it will direct us in specifying our MVP (Minimal Viable Product). Nowadays we are daily users of the different job boards understanding each one of their added values, highlighting pains and defining spaces of opportunity. \nMonth 4: Specifying product- this month will be dedicated to analyzing the results of the research and building a product that will fit the users and solve real problems.\nMonth 5: Launch MVP for proof of concept. At this stage we will have our target market and user and will know how to communicate with them. \nMonth 6-8: Improving our product based on user feedback. Understanding what was good, convenient and what was useless and friction. This will be a dynamic stage where we will hear what our users are saying, improving our product constantly and preparing for the build of our product. \nMonth 9-15: Prepare for official launch of final product. These months will be dedicated to remaking our product and system based on what we learned. At this stage we will also begin fund raising efforts. Based on a successful pilot and proof of concept we will have enough material to present investors with and increase chances of a good seed funding (+-$1MM). At this stage we will also focus on expanding the team. \nMonth 16-20: Launch 3 verticals. Those verticals will be chosen based on our research and proof of concept. We will want to create enough success stories to gain brand recognition and expand to the next verticals.\nMonth 21-24: Launch in 3 more verticals and focusing on raising Series A (+-$3MM).\nMonth 24+: Year number 3 will be about expanding into new markets, locations and products. We want to grow the development team, start creating substantial revenue and constantly improving our product and service.\n ',NULL,59,'2013-11-19 03:13:05','2013-11-19 03:13:05',9),(408,0,'Yes',NULL,59,'2013-11-19 03:14:16','2013-11-19 03:14:16',12),(409,0,'Yes',NULL,59,'2013-11-19 03:14:19','2013-11-19 03:14:19',13),(410,0,'$125',NULL,59,'2013-11-19 03:14:26','2013-11-19 03:14:26',14),(411,0,'3 months of full time engineer (roughly 540 hours)',NULL,59,'2013-11-19 03:14:31','2013-11-19 03:14:31',16),(412,0,'+- $25,000',NULL,59,'2013-11-19 03:15:28','2013-11-19 03:15:28',15),(413,0,'0',NULL,59,'2013-11-19 03:15:32','2013-11-19 03:15:32',20),(414,0,'1',NULL,59,'2013-11-19 03:15:44','2013-11-19 03:15:44',18),(415,0,'We\'re passionate about launching this startup because we feel that it will be the place where we can maximize our real potential. Working corporate jobs we find ourselves frustrated about how long processes take and the amount of bureaucracy. We\'re young, eager, energetic and hungry for success. We have been searching for ideas and pains for a while and finally feel that we a solid potential for a REAL company. A chance to create, to hire, determine culture, solve. We\'re excited about this!',NULL,59,'2013-11-19 03:26:02','2013-11-19 03:26:02',21),(416,0,'0',NULL,71,'2013-11-19 18:44:23','2013-11-19 18:44:23',17),(417,0,'Yes',NULL,71,'2013-11-19 19:05:48','2013-11-19 19:05:48',5),(418,0,'We haven\'t always been SAVVO. It all started with the realization that cofounder Joe had in grad school; almost everyone loves wine, yet very few people actually know anything about it. At that point we thought the solution would be an online wine education platform. We went into the 2012 Chicago Lean Startup Challenge, but after 10 weeks we learned some important lessons that changed our minds. In fact, we learned so much that we made it to the final four of the 107-team challenge. After talking to literally hundreds of consumers, we learned that wine education would be nice but not many people had the time, money or energy to commit to it. Instead we realized that most people just wanted to find a wine they liked without having to become an expert. They just wanted wine to be easier for them! With an overwhelming number of wines on the shelves and very little guidance in the aisle, the wine shopping experience was the real problem. Born was SAVVO.',NULL,37,'2013-11-19 22:12:52','2013-11-19 22:12:52',2),(419,0,'SAVVO is the match.com for the retail wine industry. Our mission is to find you the right wine for the right occasion, without making you have to be a wine expert to do so.because wine is supposed to be enjoyed, not feared! We are accomplishing this by making the selection process easier, more personalized and effective by deploying touch-screen wine recommending kiosks where it matters most  in the wine aisle of your favorite grocery store.',NULL,37,'2013-11-19 22:17:05','2013-11-19 22:17:05',1),(420,0,'Most of us have been here: shopping for wine, faced with 1,000s of bottles on the shelf, and no clue what wine is right for us. And, there is no one at the store available to help us. Consumers are overwhelmed, retailers cant afford to provide the much needed customer service and wine producers find it nearly impossible to differentiate themselves on the shelves. The result? A bad shopping, drinking experience for shoppers and lost revenue opportunities for retailers and suppliers.',NULL,37,'2013-11-19 22:19:33','2013-11-19 22:19:33',4),(421,0,'Most startups addressing the problem of \"wine aisle jungle confusion\" are smartphone apps. In fact, there are more than 360 apps dealing with wine. SAVVO\'s biggest differentiator: The average wine consumer (non- aficionado) is looking for help when making the buying decision in the aisle and is unlikely to have or install an app during the process. With an in-aisle kiosk we are right there WHERE and WHEN the shopper needs it most. Plus, we are inventory and price specific, adding more value.',NULL,37,'2013-11-19 22:22:59','2013-11-19 22:22:59',3),(422,0,'1) As opposed to apps (difficult to get noticed), our in aisle presence attracts shopper (user) attention and triggers impulse usage right when users need our service most 2) Innovative, cheeky signage and branding instills curiosity in core user group (females) 3) (Monetary) incentives like eCoupons or bonus points draw people to kiosk',NULL,37,'2013-11-19 22:26:29','2013-11-19 22:26:29',6),(423,1,'1) We are lacking the funds 2) to bring on or pay cutting edge UI/UX designers and developers that are necessary to build the product incorporating what we have learned through extensive in-store testing throughout recent months. Also, we 3) don\'t have the time to wait another year to build the product as we envision it, since we need to move fast on this opportunity.',NULL,37,'2013-11-19 22:29:18','2013-11-19 23:19:35',7),(424,0,'1) Fundraising: So far we have mostly bootstrapped the company. Now, we are at a point where we need to raise the seed funds to hire the talent (UI/UX and software developers) necessary to implement our product vision. This would be the best solution as it allows us to move at a fast pace which is critical for the space that we are in.\n2) Another solution is bringing on a talented UI/UX designer just in exchange for equity. Assuming that all super-talented designers either have jobs or are actively working on other projects, this will be difficult to find. However, we are exploring this option as we are speaking. Building a product this way will take substantially longer than under 1), however if necessary we will go down this path.\n',NULL,37,'2013-11-19 22:34:53','2013-11-19 22:34:53',8),(425,0,'With the lessons learned and the data collected from testing the product in smaller supermarket chains, SAVVO will be in a far better position to acquire larger, national chains. We will approach players known for their particular focus on customer service (e.g. Whole Foods, Marianos etc.) in Q2 of 2014, subsequently expanding to mass market chains like Kroger or Costco. The former are particularly suited for SAVVOs Digital Sommeliers, since these companies have already sought ways to differentiate themselves with particularly good customer service. Our goal is to have 100+ kiosks deployed, generating annual revenues of $700,000 by the end of Q3, 2014. We are looking to have nearly 2500 kiosk deployed, generating annual revenues in excess\nof $20 million, by the end of 2017. This translates into a marketshare of 7.4% of\nSAVVOs target market of 33,600 supermarkets and superstores in the US. At that point our product will have the following features:\na) Give recommendations based on past preferences and profile similarity with other users and their likes (SAVVO deems this to be the most effective way to make recommendations)\nb) Show crowd-sourced ratings and reviews by other users (and friends)\nc) Social media integration: sharing wines and reviews via Facebook, twitter, etc. d) Individual shopper login through SAVVO account or social media account (or by swiping store loyalty card) \ne) Heavy focus on visuals (instead of showing tasting notes, display graphic illustration of a wines key attributes like body, sweetness and predominant taste levels)\nf) Use proprietary SAVVO language instead of pretentious wine lingo\ng) Include brief educational nuggets for playful, simple and subtle learning\nh) Point novices to wines they are most likely to like through brief, interactive questionnaire funnels using proven non-wine analogies etc.\ni) Grant retailers, suppliers access to their individual SAVVO portal through which they can update inventory, pricing, promotion',NULL,37,'2013-11-19 22:46:58','2013-11-19 22:46:58',9),(426,0,'Cofounder came up with the idea in grad school, after having spent more than 7 years in the hospitality industry as a wine buyer and corporate restaurant manager. We made the pivot from an online wine education platform to \"decision support at point of sale\" during the Chicago Lean Startup Challenge (based on user, customer interviews and MVP prototyping)',NULL,37,'2013-11-19 22:48:29','2013-11-19 22:48:29',10),(427,0,'During the Lean Startup Challenge, summer of 2012',NULL,37,'2013-11-19 22:48:41','2013-11-19 22:48:41',11),(428,0,'Yes',NULL,37,'2013-11-19 22:48:47','2013-11-19 22:48:47',12),(429,1,'No',NULL,37,'2013-11-19 22:48:54','2013-11-19 22:49:10',13),(430,0,'300 - 350 hours ',NULL,37,'2013-11-19 22:49:51','2013-11-19 22:49:51',16),(431,0,'up to $10,000',NULL,37,'2013-11-19 22:50:10','2013-11-19 22:50:10',15),(432,1,'1',NULL,37,'2013-11-19 22:50:22','2013-11-19 22:50:57',20),(433,0,'2',NULL,37,'2013-11-19 22:50:54','2013-11-19 22:50:54',18),(434,1,'Because this is a huge and unique opportunity! Just look at the wine aisle; with thousands of bottles and no one there to help, it screams \"opportunity\". Plus, we have a vision that we love and believe in: revolutionizing the way people think about, communicate, and shop for wine by deciphering pretentious, confusing wine lingo and turn it into an easy to understand, visually focused, unique SAVVO language. Working on this is a lot of fun and drives us everyday. Literally.',NULL,37,'2013-11-19 22:58:14','2013-11-19 23:15:00',21),(435,1,'Now none, Chris is planning to transition in February',NULL,57,'2013-11-20 09:00:06','2013-11-20 12:14:13',17),(436,6,'Initially focused on the electronic music genre, LiveEx is developing a marketplace to allow creators, venues, and fans to buy, sell, and enjoy live music video content--delivering live music experiences to fans everywhere! Via a unique release window strategy and a proprietary pricing mechanism, LiveEx offers an unique opportunity to provide value to participants across the entire value chain of the live music performance ecosystem--music producers, performers, event promoters, and enthusiasts.',NULL,57,'2013-11-20 09:49:59','2013-11-20 10:01:43',1),(437,5,'As life-long music fans, we have attended hundreds of electronic music events and concerts during our lives which has allowed us to become friends with music producers, DJs, event promoters, venue owners, and other fans. These friendships provide insight into the challenges faced by independent musicians in building careers from their art. As fans who have been lucky enough to travel the world to experience our favorite artists, we see untapped demand for cutting edge music in small and mid-size venues in smaller cites. Chris\'s professional and educational experience includes film/video production, management of media and entertainment products in the online space, and analytical consulting. Boyd is an experienced entrepreneur who successfully CEO\'ed an ecommerce startup through ideation, fundraising, product development, and product launch. Our enthusiasm for the music drives our passion to create an ecosystem that will allow musicians to pursue their art and be fairly compensated.',NULL,57,'2013-11-20 10:56:51','2013-11-20 11:25:52',2),(438,1,'LiveEx offers a unique range of services and revenue streams. For services, we can perform each stage of the value chain from producing programs to securing licensing agreements to marketing video content. LiveEx\'s unique monetization strategy releases content through several VOD, streaming, subscription, and ad supported windows. We also earn fees for recording programs. We are located near music venues in LA, San Francisco, and Las Vegas and important partners like YouTube and MCNs.',NULL,57,'2013-11-20 11:26:25','2013-11-20 11:39:36',3),(439,0,'High booking fees make it difficult for event promoters in small cities or small venues to offer the best and newest artists. By scaling exhibition fees to the size of the venue, LiveEx allows fans to pay a reasonable fee to enjoy the best music--without having to get on a plane! Musicians can now grow new fan base while earning incremental revenue for the concerts they are already performing. Song producers will finally receive fair compensation for fans that hear their music in venues.',NULL,57,'2013-11-20 11:46:25','2013-11-20 11:46:25',4),(440,0,'Yes',NULL,57,'2013-11-20 11:46:25','2013-11-20 11:46:25',5),(441,1,'Direct marketing and trade advertisements to event promoters and venues, I have a list of over 2000 targets ready to go. Promoters already try to book performers for live shows through agents. Individual consumers are reached through the existing fanbase for each performer, exposure to the ad-supported content on YouTube, and advertising in music press. Direct outreach to artists, agents, and host event promoters to book new program content. DJs around the world will want to produce videos.',NULL,57,'2013-11-20 11:50:36','2013-11-20 11:53:14',6),(442,1,'(1) DRM solution (2) platform has 3 user groups (3) Santa Monica is a very competitive location to retain tech talent',NULL,57,'2013-11-20 11:54:51','2013-11-20 11:59:27',7),(443,1,'(1) I have extensively researched DRM hosting partners and negotiated a favorable rate with an industry leader. My work history at RealNetworks and MySpace video helped here. (2) I have a very thorough understanding of the user requirements, data requirements, and user flow through the transaction processes. I look forward to communicating these finding to a development team to reach creative solutions together. With international experience in consulting, I am effective and comfortable working with remote teams and different cultures. I know this will be a fun project. (3) After losing two developers to international consulting projects, I was planning to self fund a very minimal MVP that incorporated CMS, DRM, and a basic purchase form and doing everything else by hand. This is what I will do if not selected for CasuseCode. I\'m also engaged with the local incubator and startup communities looking for the right fit. i plan to raise funding for LiveEx in the next 3 months.',NULL,57,'2013-11-20 11:59:20','2013-11-20 12:03:05',8),(444,0,'Months 0-3: MVP, contracting, recording, and producing initial programs, find first seed funding\nMonths 3-6: use the above information to enter incubator or secure additional seed funding\nMonths 6-12: use proceeds to complete automated transaction platform and fund hosting environment\nYear 2: Add additional product concepts such as crowd sourced video feeds and generating MCN revenue for crowd sourced video from our events, becme and MCN for the electronic music genre\nYear 3: expand the strategy into different musical genres (indie, country, faith music) and markets (international)',NULL,57,'2013-11-20 12:08:10','2013-11-20 12:08:10',9),(445,0,'2008 while bemoaning the lack of international touring DJs in Seattle for the summer i interned for RealNetworks.',NULL,57,'2013-11-20 12:08:49','2013-11-20 12:08:49',10),(446,0,'In spring of 2008, LiveEx was a finalist in the Kellogg Cup business plan competition. The recent growth of MCN ecosystem for YouTune has provided VC interest in the consumer video space in Los Angeles. Electronic music popularity is at an all time high.',NULL,57,'2013-11-20 12:10:44','2013-11-20 12:10:44',11),(447,0,'Yes',NULL,57,'2013-11-20 12:10:54','2013-11-20 12:10:54',12),(448,2,'Yes',NULL,57,'2013-11-20 12:11:01','2013-11-20 12:11:06',13),(449,0,'$50',NULL,57,'2013-11-20 12:11:12','2013-11-20 12:11:12',14),(450,1,'Barest MVP 80 hours, MVP with automation 200 hours -- but this is a questin for engineers :)',NULL,57,'2013-11-20 12:12:07','2013-11-20 12:12:14',16),(451,1,'Planning to spend $2500-4000 -- which includes my hosting, DRM fees, and transaction processing fees',NULL,57,'2013-11-20 12:12:41','2013-11-20 12:14:12',15),(452,0,'2',NULL,57,'2013-11-20 12:14:37','2013-11-20 12:14:37',18),(453,0,'',NULL,57,'2013-11-20 12:15:54','2013-11-20 12:15:54',19),(454,2,'As previously mentioned, we are deeply invested in this musical genre and interested in supporting musicians with a thriving ecosystem. The power of musical experiences truly connect strangers, not just in physically shared space, but across communities that span the globe. LiveEx addresses interesting problems that can only be solved by new business models and technological advances. We are creating a futuristic solution for a music that is based on technology for fans for the new millennium!',NULL,57,'2013-11-20 12:19:07','2013-11-20 12:25:31',21),(455,0,'0',NULL,57,'2013-11-20 12:24:52','2013-11-20 12:24:52',20),(456,0,'Our venture involves building an online platform with two key essences:\n1. Presentation of content on an interactive map on the state of the world social & environmental level. edited by wisdom of crowds. lead to social awareness. \n2. Social engagement engine (SEE) bridge between users and organizationsor needs who require help in various fields. The platform will allow users (people/celebrities/corporate/brand) to engage with each other by offering value and perks in return for involvement. ',NULL,71,'2013-11-20 15:20:10','2013-11-20 15:20:10',1),(457,1,'1',NULL,72,'2013-11-21 02:17:35','2013-11-21 02:30:33',17),(458,2,'Yes',NULL,72,'2013-11-21 02:17:49','2013-11-21 02:23:35',5),(459,0,'Traveling is easier than ever, so why is\nknowing where to go so difficult?\n\nExisting apps leave you disconnected from\nthe local culture and reliant on paid\nadvertisements, skewed reviews and\noutdated guidebooks.\n\nToo often the experiences you plan dont\nend up close to what was expected,\nwasting your time & money.\n\nWhy not travel like a local?',NULL,72,'2013-11-21 02:19:17','2013-11-21 02:19:17',1),(460,1,'ingollow is creating authentic social relationships between locals & travelers and businesses in a geographic area through social networking and\nsocial commerce enterprise.',NULL,72,'2013-11-21 02:23:02','2013-11-21 02:23:56',4),(461,0,'That is part of the ingollow IP, outlined in our pitch deck and business plan.',NULL,72,'2013-11-21 02:23:28','2013-11-21 02:23:28',6),(462,0,'ingollow is an all-in-one app that connects to current social plug-ins for both the users and businesses. We culled the best practices and integrated the\nmissed opportunities of our competitors and added even more useful features!\n\nFor users, ingollow is the perfect platform to travel like a local.\n\nFor businesses, ingollow is the perfect platform to reach new customers and to reward loyal ones.',NULL,72,'2013-11-21 02:25:07','2013-11-21 02:25:07',3),(463,0,'We love to travel and to explore, sharing the best places to find, do, or good eats to try.\n\nHowever when we leave our known areas it left us with this question...Traveling is easier than ever, so why is knowing where to go so difficult?\n\nExisting apps leave you disconnected from the local culture and reliant on paid advertisements, skewed reviews and outdated guidebooks.\n\nWhy not travel like a local, go, do, see and share what the locals know of any given area or destination.',NULL,72,'2013-11-21 02:25:23','2013-11-21 02:25:23',2),(464,0,'Funding, building and growing the team. Finding mentors.',NULL,72,'2013-11-21 02:25:51','2013-11-21 02:25:51',7),(465,0,'Lern more from the start-up community in the Boston area.',NULL,72,'2013-11-21 02:26:15','2013-11-21 02:26:15',8),(466,1,'Feb 2012 1hile on vacation in Hawaii, incorporated the company on 31 Jul 2013',NULL,72,'2013-11-21 02:27:08','2013-11-21 02:28:26',10),(467,1,'Started everything on 15 SEP',NULL,72,'2013-11-21 02:27:17','2013-11-21 02:27:24',11),(468,0,'Phase 1:\n 6 months  build proof of concept in Oahu\n 1 year  expand to all of Hawaiian Islands\n\nPhase 2:\n Expand to Boston, Tokyo, Seoul, Las Vegas\n\nPhase 3:\n New York City, D.C., Miam',NULL,72,'2013-11-21 02:29:19','2013-11-21 02:29:19',9),(469,0,'Yes',NULL,72,'2013-11-21 02:29:23','2013-11-21 02:29:23',12),(470,0,'Yes',NULL,72,'2013-11-21 02:29:27','2013-11-21 02:29:27',13),(471,0,'$100.00',NULL,72,'2013-11-21 02:29:37','2013-11-21 02:29:37',14),(472,0,'$30-$50K',NULL,72,'2013-11-21 02:29:54','2013-11-21 02:29:54',15),(473,0,'300 Hours',NULL,72,'2013-11-21 02:30:19','2013-11-21 02:30:19',16),(474,0,'0',NULL,72,'2013-11-21 02:30:26','2013-11-21 02:30:26',20),(475,0,'1',NULL,72,'2013-11-21 02:30:39','2013-11-21 02:30:39',18),(476,0,'My passions are in traveling and exploring. The market is flooded with apps that allow you to book the best flight and lodging...However there is nothing out there that allows you to interact with the locals and businesses in a geographic area. Why not travel like a local, find the things you want to do based on your interest and needs.',NULL,72,'2013-11-21 02:32:56','2013-11-21 02:32:56',21),(477,0,'https://drive.google.com/a/ingollow.com/?tab=wo#folders/0B4tomQ16S_PITE5nc2U5bHM0dHM',NULL,72,'2013-11-21 02:33:12','2013-11-21 02:33:12',19),(478,8,'27 years on this earth makes you wonder about what we accomplished & evolved as a species, yet we ponder on where everything is going from here..we created this amazingly advanced civilisation-Technology,the internet, Capitalism,Architecture,Democracy,Social networks, Wikipedia, smartphones,  advertisement,Apps,banks,celebrities,the Moon,Higgs particle.. Never the less what about global warming,economical crisis,diminishing natural resources, cries for help,natural disasters,endangered animals,oil spills,Africa,human footprint etc. We all hear about environmentally deteriorating situation of the world, the social misfortune and lack of balance around the globe.Am I doing enough?The answer is no.But why?Human nature.I don\'t get value for engaging. My individual life is hard as it is.Awareness & Responsibility is Key and we intend to bring it quantified value. The vision of our venture is not only creating an innovative parallel economic-social system but pursue a civilisational leap.  ',NULL,71,'2013-11-21 03:05:09','2013-11-27 22:09:31',2),(479,3,'By harnessing wisdom of the crowds & the power of social networks our mission is creating the future hub of quality scientific & educational content with an Engaging Engine addressing what is common to all of us-world state of environmental & social issues. Fuelling it with innovative interactive UI,users  influencing & motivating other users around the globe by introducing value exchange,creating an alternate GlobalCoin mine by engaging good, & providing brands an innovative advertising model.',NULL,71,'2013-11-21 03:14:11','2013-11-27 22:15:44',3),(480,1,'Our venture is key in shaping the tomorrow as it propose a new model of taking responsibility as a collective in SN shell. Typhoon in the Philippines example-Tens of thousands call for help. Instantly countless needs are created, waiting for response.You see it on the news & most likely continue with your capitalistic day.The platform as an arena where corporate/brands/SME\'s/celebrities/people could take responsibility on local & global needs by motivating engagement & receiving quantified value',NULL,71,'2013-11-21 03:27:58','2013-11-21 03:50:47',4),(481,0,'0',NULL,58,'2013-11-25 01:58:09','2013-11-25 01:58:09',17),(482,0,'0',NULL,76,'2013-11-25 04:08:34','2013-11-25 04:08:34',17),(483,1,'3 out of 4 people choose death over speaking in front of a crowd. Were building a social feedback community designed to help people improve their speech & presentation delivery. The community is a safe place for users to prepare, practice, and get feedback from the other members & experts before standing in front of the real audience, when the moment counts and the stakes are high. Thru the courage & encouragement circle, we aim to help individuals find confidence in their message & themselves',NULL,76,'2013-11-25 10:56:42','2013-11-29 18:35:00',1),(484,1,'We started out with the idea of creating an app that tracks oratory metrics and helps users be aware of their ums, uh, like while speaking. The goal of the app was to raise personal awareness so that users can start addressing their areas of weakness and be more effective communicators. As we started thinking about how to monetize the app, we realized that though the idea had merits, an app by itself isnt a sustainable business model. \n\nAs timing would have it, while we were trying to come up with ways to make the app idea sustainable, we discovered that Startup Weekend NEXT was offering a 5-week course in Dallas the following week. Without hesitation, we signed up for the class. In learning the lean startup concept from Steve Blank, talking to veteran entrepreneurs, and going through the customer discovery phase by actually talking to and getting feedback from more than 1,000 customers, our idea expanded beyond the original app concept and evolved into a social network concept. \n',NULL,76,'2013-11-25 10:56:43','2013-11-29 18:35:13',2),(485,1,'We havent seen another startup like ours & the current market of helping people be better speakers is segmented. Personal coaches fill this market by offering 1-on-1 service for a limited time. The other company that is similar to us is Toastmasters. But Toastmasters model is outdated & is losing membership. Our idea utilizes the power of crowd to help ppl be better speakers. Its also an aggregating portal for coaches to reach clients worldwide, such as users who desire the 1-on-1 coaching.',NULL,76,'2013-11-25 10:56:44','2013-11-29 18:35:25',3),(486,1,'We all have ideas & thoughts we want to communicate, but very few of us can do so effectively, especially in a crowd setting. Many ppl are afraid of public speaking because they lack the techniques & they worry what the audience thinks of them. By offering access to a mass audience before the real audience, users will have a safe place to get feedback & know how theyre being perceived. Consequently, users will be more effective & confident in their message & themselves before standing on stage.',NULL,76,'2013-11-25 10:56:45','2013-11-29 18:35:40',4),(487,4,'Start with the 114 evangelists obtained thru the surveys\nExpand thru referral programs (snowball effect)\nPartners program\nProfessors & other sites that offer complimentary service  Strategically position ourselves to allow these two groups to leverage our website as a way to further engage students/clients and help them get more from the learning process\nSocial network & ads channels\nUltimately, the best way to attract, keep, and grow the user base is by offering free trials & a quality program',NULL,76,'2013-11-25 10:56:48','2013-11-29 18:35:49',6),(488,0,'Yes',NULL,76,'2013-11-25 05:26:54','2013-11-25 05:26:54',5),(489,1,'1) Building a MVP  neither of the founders is a programmer or has a technical background\n2) Find enough users to test MVP\n3) Repeat & Scale',NULL,76,'2013-11-25 10:59:41','2013-11-29 18:36:04',7),(490,1,'1) Technology will play a critical role in supporting our value proposition when we launch, but at this stage, our main focus in building the MVP is to test & validate the crowd support concept. Our challenge is to validate whether ppl would benefit from our service. Ideally, itd be wonderful to have a MVP that simulates the real website environment & incorporates some of the gamification features. But because we currently dont have a programmer, we plan on using a private Youtube channel as a way for users to upload their recordings, engage one another in feedback, & follow up with users on the actual results after their real speech \n2) Were reaching out to the 114 people who left their contact info during the surveys to be participants. We also have a friend who is a communications professor & has volunteered his students to test our MVP\n3) Depending on the MVP results, we will launch Rhetorist in 2014. In overcoming the challenge of driving traffic to the website  were going to identify key partners (coaches & professors) & create a program that would mutually benefit both parties. Another critical piece in driving traffic is identifying the distribution channels for ads & affiliate programs. To keep users engaged & returninggamification will be key & were creating different features such as levels, rating, prizes, etc. to incorporate into the website. To get users to repeatedly payfostering a safe environment w/ quality feedback from members will be key\n',NULL,76,'2013-11-25 10:59:42','2013-11-29 18:45:47',8),(491,1,'From a 50,000 ft perspective, our road map for the next 3 years are as follow:\n1) Acquire, maintain, and grow user base\n2) Monetize\n3) Funding to grow company\n4) Roll out an app (there are several reasons behind this, one is to assist speakers during the real speech/presentation, another is to lower the barrier of uploading their recordings)\n5) Refine technology  One of components for our vision is to allow users options on how they want to get feedback from the community. They can either upload their recordings or videos or deliver their speech/presentation live with other attendees listening. With any of these scenarios, we want to get to the point where we could simulate the real environment (being on stage, in front of a classroom, sitting in a conference room). The idea behind this is that if could replicate the real environment as much as possible, speakers should feel more at ease when theyre on the real stage \n\nFrom the ground perspective (this is not a comprehensive list of activities that we would do in any year, this is to highlight the main points). Note: it can be expected that some of our strategies may change due to changes in the environment.\n\n2014\nBuild & test MVP\nIdentify & talk with key partners\nIdentify distribution channels\nPut structure around the gamification process\nAdvertising \nBlog\nLaunch on a small scale\n\n2015\nHire & retain talents\nBuild companys culture\nAdvertising \nAcquire new users, keep current users engaged\nTrack metrics & milestones\nTrack benefits on users\nRefine gamification process\nRoll out app\nQuality control\nBlog \n\n2016\nHire & retain talents\nBuild companys culture\nContinue to refine technology\nBuild & maintain relationships with partners\nContinue to keep, maintain, and grow user base\nTrack metrics & milestones\nRefine gamification process\nAdvertising \nQuality control\nTrack benefits on users\nBlog\n',NULL,76,'2013-11-25 10:59:44','2013-11-29 18:46:33',9),(492,1,'August 2013',NULL,76,'2013-11-25 10:59:47','2013-11-29 18:46:37',10),(493,1,'November 2013',NULL,76,'2013-11-25 10:59:49','2013-11-29 18:46:41',11),(494,1,'No',NULL,76,'2013-11-25 11:01:17','2013-11-29 18:46:53',12),(495,2,'Yes',NULL,76,'2013-11-25 11:01:18','2013-11-29 18:47:11',13),(496,1,'22',NULL,76,'2013-11-25 11:01:24','2013-11-29 18:47:43',16),(497,1,'<$2000',NULL,76,'2013-11-25 11:01:26','2013-11-29 18:47:47',15),(498,0,'0',NULL,76,'2013-11-25 05:33:18','2013-11-25 05:33:18',20),(499,0,'1',NULL,76,'2013-11-25 05:33:32','2013-11-25 05:33:32',18),(500,1,'Effective communication is critical to any1 who wants to connect, relate, & share their ideas w/ others. As the world shifts towards the digital space, the ability to articulately deliver a msg in front of groups is becoming a lost art. When you ponder on it, how many great ideas are lost because the speaker could not convey the importance and excitement of their idea to the audience? We find this to be a shame & hope we can make a difference in helping ppl effectively communicate their passion',NULL,76,'2013-11-25 11:03:36','2013-11-29 18:49:20',21),(501,1,'1',NULL,14,'2013-11-25 08:15:24','2013-11-25 08:57:47',17),(502,0,'Share with and borrow from your friends, or rent to and loan from the public; AirBnB for all of your possessions. Track what your friends have borrowed, be reminded of what you have yet to return.',NULL,14,'2013-11-25 08:32:05','2013-11-25 08:32:05',1),(503,2,'HeyCanI was created when I found myself lacking the correct tool in the middle of car dissection. I didn\'t want to spam facebook, but needed to know if any of my friends had something that would work... Lacking that ability, I came up with HeyCanI, and the idea developed from there. Right now we are still in the initial stages of a bootstrapped startup, but are looking to develop quickly.',NULL,14,'2013-11-25 08:34:31','2013-11-25 08:35:27',2),(504,1,'The idea is a pretty novel one; short of car-sharing services, or AirBnB, there is not much in the field.. Closest competitors would be sports rental stores, or tool/hardware rental shops.',NULL,14,'2013-11-25 08:36:39','2013-11-25 08:36:45',3),(505,0,'Sharing is a concept available to society since primitive times. It allows a trusting group of individuals to all benefit from an investment by one. While the internet has enhanced many aspects of life today, has it affected the way we share with our friends? \n\n The purpose of HeyCanI is to take the next step forward: Allowing one to easily share their possessions, letting friends borrow, as well as borrow what their friends have available. ',NULL,14,'2013-11-25 08:39:42','2013-11-25 08:39:42',4),(506,0,'Yes',NULL,14,'2013-11-25 08:39:46','2013-11-25 08:39:46',5),(507,0,'HeyCanI plans on acquiring a userbase by providing an amazing and useful service, through a streamlined and painless UI, throwing in aspects of gamification to keep users involved beyond initial signup. ',NULL,14,'2013-11-25 08:41:31','2013-11-25 08:41:31',6),(508,0,'When I started  on the business plan and realized how large of an idea this was. ',NULL,14,'2013-11-25 08:42:46','2013-11-25 08:42:46',11),(509,0,'It is difficult to find good designers and developers with time available to work on a bootstrapped project (read: for equity). Can that count for two?  :)\n\nAlso having a clear idea of market size/potential share is difficult when it is such a broad concept.',NULL,14,'2013-11-25 08:45:53','2013-11-25 08:45:53',7),(510,0,'Winning this opportunity. \n\nRegarding market size, I will probably leave it out of my business plan, and focus on metrics generated by initial keyword jaunts in google adwords, or on a small landing page. I would instead focus on generated, calculated interest than potential \'pie in the sky\' projections. \n\n',NULL,14,'2013-11-25 08:48:28','2013-11-25 08:48:28',8),(511,1,'Depending on the interest generated, year 3 would have us closing our second round of funding Ideally. \n\nRealistically, I would say year one would be spent creating a stable product and starting a public beta. Year two would be monetization and marketing... Monetization through taking a cut of public \'rent/loan\' transactions. Year three would be looking to expand, and start research on best ways to accelerate growth. ',NULL,14,'2013-11-25 08:50:57','2013-11-25 08:52:52',9),(512,0,'I needed a tool midway through a little car project (Factory Five GTM) and didn\'t know who had one available. I thought: \"How can I create something to resolve this problem?\'',NULL,14,'2013-11-25 08:54:16','2013-11-25 08:54:16',10),(513,0,'Yes',NULL,14,'2013-11-25 08:54:31','2013-11-25 08:54:31',12),(514,0,'Yes',NULL,14,'2013-11-25 08:54:33','2013-11-25 08:54:33',13),(515,0,'$100',NULL,14,'2013-11-25 08:54:44','2013-11-25 08:54:44',14),(516,0,'50 for GUI, 50 for database, 50 for backend. x5 if we\'re talking realistically.',NULL,14,'2013-11-25 08:56:43','2013-11-25 08:56:43',16),(517,0,'I would be willing to invest about $25 million. How much do I have available? Not $25M :)',NULL,14,'2013-11-25 08:57:41','2013-11-25 08:57:41',15),(518,0,'0',NULL,14,'2013-11-25 08:57:55','2013-11-25 08:57:55',20),(519,0,'1',NULL,14,'2013-11-25 08:58:01','2013-11-25 08:58:01',18),(520,0,'I want to do this startup because this would solve a problem people are faced with daily, myself included. It would change commerce, and build stronger bonds between friends and communities. It would give people opportunities that they wouldn\'t have otherwise. ',NULL,14,'2013-11-25 09:03:32','2013-11-25 09:03:32',21),(521,0,'Render provides safety for the crowd by the crowd.  Our simple and intuitive mobile app tracks crowd sourced user data in an instance of mass violence and literally renders the situation visually, enabling first responders and risk management to track the emergency as it develops in real time.  ',NULL,41,'2013-11-26 07:58:38','2013-11-26 07:58:38',1),(522,5,'The concept of Render is a direct result of a Social Entrepreneurship class at the University of North Texas.  As current students, we felt compelled to address campus shootings and immediately began developing the concept of a simple smartphone application that could enable students to help themselves in the event of mass violence while aiding first responders by visually depicting the situation for quick analysis.  The Render team asked ourselves what we wanted, as students and potential victims, in the occurrence of an active shooter on campus. We decided to harness two key characteristics of our humanity, the impulse to control ones surroundings and the incredible power of dense communication.  In addition, we see potential in Renders future to aid in larger instances of mass violence and hope that the app will translate to the general population so areas that suffer frequent terrorist attacks will have the ability to connect with each other and better navigate the situation.',NULL,41,'2013-11-26 08:00:55','2013-11-28 01:15:05',2),(523,2,'Render is a unique mobile app that takes a decentralized approach to crisis management by allowing a user to send an alert to surrounding users in the instance of mass violence. Existing personal safety apps merely connect a single user with the police or a personalized contact group. Current apps have a centralized, one-way approach to notification while Render is decentralized, making it more time-effective.  We have done extensive competitor analysis and are confident Render remains distinct.',NULL,41,'2013-11-26 08:10:35','2013-11-28 01:17:54',3),(524,4,'The average active shooter incident lasts 12.5 minutes while the average university response time takes about 18 minutes.  Currently, our campus notification system takes at least 10 minutes to reach the student community. It is very likely that in the event of a school shooting, risk management authorities will be informed of the event after the events conclusion. Render empowers the people most qualified to send a timely alert and warn their fellow students, those in immediate proximity.  ',NULL,41,'2013-11-26 08:10:52','2013-11-28 01:18:33',4),(525,0,'Yes',NULL,41,'2013-11-26 08:19:07','2013-11-26 08:19:07',5),(526,0,'0',NULL,85,'2013-11-27 05:48:56','2013-11-27 05:48:56',17),(527,0,'As individual & collective responsibility is key & with high correlation, we will provide on one end the need, feeling & recognition of an individual or entity to be part of something larger than itself (see Kony 2012 campaign).On the other end provide the users as brands big corporate SME\'s or celebrities to use their power & influence to Motivate users to engage with the world\'s needs by offering value or Sponsor needs, thus gaining recognition on converging power & influence to responsibility',NULL,71,'2013-11-27 17:31:50','2013-11-27 17:31:50',6),(528,5,'1. The need of a strong technology side as a fonder-this is no app. we need Backend/Server-Side,Client-Side,Mobile development, algorithm development. we interview technology ninjas from the Israeli technology units but its hard to compete with huge salaries they are offered from corporates. \n2. Meeting money before we establish a strong teem. \n3. making the \"game\" cool and worth watching ',NULL,71,'2013-11-27 17:42:58','2013-11-27 18:29:20',7),(529,16,'1. Engaging with great opportunities like CauseCode. \n2. As a strategy we are constantly pursuing great people to join our megalomaniacal venture before we meet money.This is a venture for more than two minds. we seek people interested to be a part of history and change the world. Once a worthy teem will be recruited and will have a demo to show there would be a lot of investors interested in being a part of this venture (we already have some in line)\n3. Building the \"game\" is a term we use to describe the chronology of creating this venture.S1, develop the concept of the game and its rules. check! S2, building the stadium-The infrastructure of the platform.The novel UI of presenting the state/vital signs/pulse of the world environmentally & socially, on an interactive map which purpose is to raise the awareness & knowledge of the audience and the recognition of action & engagement (the field). The social network (the stadium stands viewing the field). The engaging engine (\"slides\" form the stands to the field)-This is the complexity of the venture as it involves the link between the frame to realty, this includes a mobile app that will allow a location base engagement to needs around the user in accordance to his skills preferences social circles and special offers.The add space around the field is how brands,corporations,SME\'s & celebrities will motivate engagement with perks & sponsor activities.S3, market the game to brands, celebrities etc. S4, launch (open the games).',NULL,71,'2013-11-27 17:53:22','2013-11-27 21:51:14',8),(530,2,'around 8 months ago  ',NULL,71,'2013-11-27 18:22:15','2013-11-27 18:22:52',10),(531,0,'6 months ago.',NULL,71,'2013-11-27 18:22:40','2013-11-27 18:22:40',11),(532,18,'Initial infrastructure of the platform will take approximately 6 months. 1.Creating the interactive map where the \"game\" will be played-GIS system, crowd edit & interactive UI to raise awareness & action by presenting the worlds status,\"needs\", recognition of users involvement & their impact on the world 2.Social network features 3.The packages system (connecting needs, motivators/sponsors and people) in which nonprofits/charities/NGO\'s acting in aid of environmental and social challenges will upload & present their needs & ongoing projects around users will interact with each other-the package will present the needs in funding, human skills/power & larger needs suitable for sponsors.After a package is competed it will be anchored for life on the interactive world map where all users involved, the accomplishment & impact will be presented with their profile picture and relevant info regarding their contribution. 4.Creating the Coin concept & system-the platform will introduce it\'s own motivation for involvement to all users as a virtual coin called GC (globe coin/good coin).Every package will have a currency-GC@h & GC@$. The currency will be determined by an algorithm that will change the currency of packages in accordance of ask and demand. Users will mine this coin by acting and engaging with the the needs. \n6 months of introducing the platform to 2 key users: 1.\"motivators & sponsor\" users such as brands,corporations,sites (museums, theme-parks etc.) & influencers (celebrities, athlete,opinion leaders,business people,politicians etc.) 2. Training nonprofits/charities/NGO\'s.Years 2-3 increase in user traffic,subscribers,motivators & nonprofits as the platform become more viral & independent.Platform become an innovative advertising model to brands/corporation/SME\'s,a hub of social pressure, quality index & CV. New packages to both the young & Gray market.\"motivated\" counting gains importance as \"followers\" in SocialN\'s. GC a legitimate means of payment. apps.\n\n',NULL,71,'2013-12-01 19:20:44','2013-12-02 23:29:02',9),(533,0,'Yes',NULL,71,'2013-11-27 21:52:31','2013-11-27 21:52:31',12),(534,0,'Yes',NULL,71,'2013-11-27 21:52:38','2013-11-27 21:52:38',13),(535,0,'50',NULL,71,'2013-11-27 21:52:46','2013-11-27 21:52:46',14),(536,2,'1740',NULL,71,'2013-11-27 21:54:41','2013-11-27 21:55:21',16),(537,0,'100,000',NULL,71,'2013-11-27 21:56:10','2013-11-27 21:56:10',15),(538,0,'1',NULL,71,'2013-11-27 21:56:35','2013-11-27 21:56:35',18),(539,7,'Imagining the future is inherent in us as we believe our venture will affect & shape the future world & the people who call it home. Imagine a world where class is not measured only by power, popularity or individual success but how you harness those to motivate others & act to better the world while being a part of a parallel economy. Imagine that to get applied for a job or Academy will be additionally conditioned on your quality score. What is your quality score? What have u left behind? ',NULL,71,'2013-11-29 07:01:37','2013-12-04 18:25:35',21),(540,0,'0',NULL,71,'2013-11-27 22:06:54','2013-11-27 22:06:54',20),(541,0,'A large installed user base is critical for Render\'s functionality.  In Phase 1, we will sell Render to large universities and allow each institution to deploy our app to the 100s of safety officers and RAs who are required to respond in a crisis.  The Universities we\'ve consulted with are very excited to bring Render to their campus.  Phase 2, branch out to large events/institution, i.e. marathons. Phase 3, move to the public, especially places with high violence and daily domestic terrorism.',NULL,41,'2013-11-28 01:30:57','2013-11-28 01:30:57',6),(542,0,'Hackers. Time. Complexity. We are broke college students and do not have the resources to build our app.  We have exhausted our local tech community with no luck.  Although we are trying to teach ourselves how to code, the learning process will take far too long and Render is something the world needs NOW.  The backend of Render is complex and will need expert input to succeed in a crisis. ',NULL,41,'2013-11-28 01:36:07','2013-11-28 01:36:07',7),(543,0,'We have taught ourselves how to wireframe our app and design the UIUX.  This will allow us to give excellent direction to the app developers we bring on.  We\'re working with our university\'s Association for Information Sciences to build the Microsoft platform of Render for the Imagine Cup.  However, we will need an Android and iOS version before we can receive funding or investor attention.  We would love to bring on an app developer but unfortunately, we haven\'t been able to find a competent iOS or Android developer within the student population.  We\'ve decided that our best option is to hire an app developer to round our our platform suite.  Honestly- over the next few months, our CEO is going to sell her car and our other cofounders are combining credit cards and all of our savings to fund the iOS development.  After we have an iOS version, we will approach our local angle community (our CEO is an intern at the North Texas Angel Network) then we can use the funding we receive to develop the Android version.  We will have to sacrifice equity to get the necessary funding. Time is the ultimate factor in our strategy.  We would like to bring Render to market as quickly as possible. ',NULL,41,'2013-11-28 01:59:38','2013-11-28 01:59:38',8),(544,0,'05/2013',NULL,41,'2013-11-28 02:00:11','2013-11-28 02:00:11',10),(545,0,'05/2013',NULL,41,'2013-11-28 02:00:33','2013-11-28 02:00:33',11),(546,1,'ADD!!!!!! When Clarissa feels better ;)',NULL,41,'2013-11-28 02:00:38','2013-11-28 02:48:42',9),(547,0,'Yes',NULL,41,'2013-11-28 02:00:44','2013-11-28 02:00:44',12),(548,0,'Yes',NULL,41,'2013-11-28 02:00:48','2013-11-28 02:00:48',13),(549,1,'$15',NULL,41,'2013-11-28 02:01:07','2013-11-28 02:01:16',14),(550,1,'We\'ve been quoted about 300hrs by several app developers.  ',NULL,41,'2013-11-28 02:02:39','2013-11-28 02:02:59',16),(551,0,'Everything we have.  Time. Money. Everything. We\'ve currently agreed to contribute about 2,000 each (all we have saved) = 6,000',NULL,41,'2013-11-28 02:05:35','2013-11-28 02:05:35',15),(552,0,'0',NULL,41,'2013-11-28 02:06:33','2013-11-28 02:06:33',18),(553,0,'0',NULL,41,'2013-11-28 02:07:11','2013-11-28 02:07:11',20),(554,0,'We want to make the crowd an engine for safety.  On average, a mass shooting occurs every two weeks in the US.  Campus\' and crowded areas are frequent targets of terrorism.  The current centralized approach to mass text notification is solitary and fractured, providing little data to the population in danger and the first responders. Render can revolutionized the way we respond in a crisis, making it a collective effort.  We can make the crowd an active element in crisis management. ',NULL,41,'2013-11-28 02:41:02','2013-11-28 02:41:02',21),(555,0,'$10',NULL,76,'2013-11-29 18:47:32','2013-11-29 18:47:32',14),(556,0,'https://www.dropbox.com/s/rl8zijqlxkl4we0/500Hrs%20Deck.pdf',NULL,76,'2013-11-29 18:48:49','2013-11-29 18:48:49',19),(557,0,'0',NULL,95,'2013-12-02 09:29:40','2013-12-02 09:29:40',17),(558,0,'Yes',NULL,95,'2013-12-02 09:30:28','2013-12-02 09:30:28',5),(559,0,'0',NULL,96,'2013-12-03 02:05:11','2013-12-03 02:05:11',17),(560,8,'In July of 2011, Nate Houghton was preparing for a trip to Africa. He had just graduated from college, was living in a dumpy rented room in a dumpy apartment in Queens, NY, and working the most boring phone sales job you can imagine. He was new in the area and still learning his way around.\n\nTraveling to Africa requires a few simple chores. Nate needed to get passport photos, malaria medication, shampoo, and snacks. After 35 minutes of searching, Nate had little to show for his efforts but 7 browser tabs cross-referencing convenience store locations, subway lines, and store hours. Nate was not happy. He thought that there had to be a better way.\n\nHe immediately emailed his technologist college buddy with the title \"Does this exist?\" His friend didn\'t even bother to email back. He called immediately. Sereal was born.\n\nNearly three years later, after various twists and turns, the team is ready to build Sereal.',NULL,85,'2013-12-04 23:06:22','2013-12-05 01:24:03',2),(561,8,'Sereal rapidly connects people with the things they need by mapping inventory for consumer use. Currently, inventory mapping tools are at once inadequate and overwhelming. Hundreds of results are presented for single items and there is no option to allow for searches of multiple products at once.\n\nFor consumers, Sereal is a way to run errands faster and spend more time using products instead of finding them. For retailers, Sereal is the most efficient way to get products in front of consumers.\n',NULL,85,'2013-12-04 23:12:53','2013-12-05 01:23:45',1),(562,6,'Sereal is unique because it will allow users to conduct accurate inventory-level searches of multiple goods at once. Mapping applications are very advanced, but existing inventory-level searches are inadequate, especially for consumables. Further, no application allows users to search for lists of multiple items at once.\n\nSereal will be the first application that integrates a to-do list filled with a consumers items with a map to retrieve these items. ',NULL,85,'2013-12-04 12:31:17','2013-12-05 01:24:44',3),(563,6,'Sereal impacts the world by quickening the pace of commerce and adding market transparency.\n\nFor consumers, a pain point currently exists when seeking particular items, or a list of items, that may exist in disparate locations. Sereal allows consumers to find these items quickly and easily.\n\nFor retailers, identifying consumers by location prior to their purchasing decision is the primary pain point. Sereal allows retailers to learn about consumer behavior outside of the store.\n',NULL,85,'2013-12-04 12:31:27','2013-12-05 01:25:12',4),(564,0,'No',NULL,85,'2013-12-03 03:31:27','2013-12-03 03:31:27',5),(565,5,'1) Overcoming the first challenge is simple: it will require a great deal of hard (and boring) work by a very efficient team. The key is to truly bootstrap a minimum viable product in a defined geographic area that solves a problem for enough users to attract attention. User adoption creates Sereals value through both data and advertising. This will open doors to retailers, which will then make it possible to improve the quality of product and acquire more users. Additionally, APIs are currently available at no cost from other inventory search products.\n\n2) To avoid the negative effects of the second challenge, Sereal will not strive to be the largest database of inventory, but will strive to deliver the most useful result to every consumer. Without a doubt, there will be times that the results are not accurate, but the application will be built in an iterative manner such that it improves consistently. \n\n3) Sereals iterative nature will allow users to truly think of it as their application, meaning that it will consistently improve its ability to understand and even anticipate their needs. Certainly, the application will be difficult for users initially, but it will improve for every user with uses. ',NULL,85,'2013-12-05 02:23:56','2013-12-05 01:27:43',8),(566,1,'Q1 of 2014\n    Conduct market research through survey data to determine user interest in Manhattan.\n    Begin to build alpha version.\n    Create signup form and partner with 100 local Manhattan retailers selling consumables.\n    Market research to learn consumer behavior when making shopping lists.\n\nQ2 of 2014\n    Complete and launch alpha version with 250 Manhattan retailers selling consumables.\n    Continued market research to learn consumer behavior when making shopping lists.\n\nQ3 and Q4 of 2014\n    Users complete at least 100 average daily searches in Manhattan.\n    Refine product based on user feedback.\n    Reach 500 Manhattan partner retailers.\n\nQ1 of 2015\n    Launch and advertise a limited beta.\n    Begin raising a seed round from angel investors, incubators, and other sources.\n    Establish 10 national retailer partnerships.\n    Users complete at least 500 average daily searches in Manhattan.\n\nQ2 and Q3 of 2015\n    Raise a seed round of $750,000.\n    Grow the team beyond founders.\n    Conduct market research through survey data to determine user interest nationally. \n\nQ4 of 2015\n    Establish 20 new national retailer partnerships.\n    Launch second and third metro areas.\n    Users complete 8,000 average daily searches nationwide. \n\nQ1 and Q2 of 2016\n    Raise funding round of $3 million.\n    Launch fourth through eighth metro areas.\n    Users complete 15,000 average daily searches nationwide.\n\nQ3 and Q4 of 2016\n    Ten advertising sales for revenue.\n    Three data mapping sales for revenue.\n    Launch ninth through twentieth metro areas.\n    Users complete 30,000 average daily searches nationwide.',NULL,85,'2013-12-04 04:25:21','2013-12-05 01:29:24',9),(567,0,'2011',NULL,85,'2013-12-03 22:55:23','2013-12-03 22:55:23',10),(568,1,'Last month',NULL,85,'2013-12-04 04:25:29','2013-12-05 01:29:27',11),(569,3,'1) Building a user base without retailer partnerships. There will be challenges with building a useful product without an API.\n\n2) Inventory accuracy, especially from small retailers. Maintaining an inventory list will be difficult.\n\n3) Search accuracy from each user. Sereal will seek to be very efficient for consumers listing products to purchase, meaning that some terms will be difficult.',NULL,85,'2013-12-04 15:25:34','2013-12-05 01:26:42',7),(570,1,'300',NULL,85,'2013-12-04 04:26:16','2013-12-05 01:29:51',16),(571,1,'Yes',NULL,85,'2013-12-04 04:26:16','2013-12-05 01:29:51',13),(572,0,'Yes',NULL,85,'2013-12-03 22:56:19','2013-12-03 22:56:19',12),(573,1,'$100,000',NULL,85,'2013-12-04 04:26:25','2013-12-05 01:29:26',15),(574,1,'3',NULL,102,'2013-12-05 05:21:11','2013-12-05 00:52:25',17),(575,1,'LifeDojo delivers fun, science-based online classes directly to students and clients, so front line professionals can get back to what they do best - 1on1 counselling and support. LifeDojo is the Lynda.com for health and life skills. Trusted by over 120 institutions and 11,000 users, we deliver classes online using whiteboard animations, quizzes, and lesson plans that fit any institutional goal. Our customers rely on LifeDojo not just to teach, but to lead students to positive lifestyle change',NULL,102,'2013-12-05 05:43:03','2013-12-05 01:07:33',1),(576,0,'0',NULL,103,'2013-12-05 00:14:29','2013-12-05 00:14:29',17),(577,0,'Chris launched LifeDojo after years of working in healthcare, nonprofit and education -- and seeing a clear pain point among his colleagues and employees.\n\nThere are over 5 million professionals in the US today whose job it is to teach health & life skills to other people. They are tasked with the near-impossible job of changing how other people behave in measurable ways. Corporate wellness instructors are seeking less sick days and higher employee motivation. Healthcare educators are seeking lower health risk behavior, more exercise and better nutrition. Nonprofits and schools are looking to reduce risky behavior in youth, increase study skills, social skills, leadership skills and more. In all cases, the front-line professionals teaching these topics fail to succeed -- and often blame themselves for that failure. What became clear was the overwhelming need for an online support platform that taught every life skill in an engaging, science-based way. Having massive social impact.',NULL,102,'2013-12-05 00:15:50','2013-12-05 00:15:50',2),(578,1,'Our major competitors are Everfi.com and Udemy.com.\n\nEverfi teaches Critical Skills in the K-12 market using online programs, though their fatal flaw is in the tone of their content. The tone they teach in is \"parent-to-child\". This may sound trivial, but people generally hate being told what to do and how to improve habits. \n\nUdemy\'s classes are community created, with very little curation for quality. \n\nWe have expertly designed high-quality content, communicated by world-class experts.',NULL,102,'2013-12-05 05:52:07','2013-12-05 01:10:28',3),(579,0,'LifeDojo is a tool that will improve health and life outcomes of users, and improve the success outcomes of the institutions who pay for it. See above\n\nLifeDojo is nothing short of a major disruption in a series of verticals that are largely untouched by modern technology interventions. A vast majority of professionals still rely on a combination of 1) text-based life skills curriculum, 2) limited professional development, and 3) expensive, outsourced support for critical moment interventions.',NULL,102,'2013-12-05 00:26:04','2013-12-05 00:26:04',4),(580,0,'Yes',NULL,102,'2013-12-05 00:26:10','2013-12-05 00:26:10',5),(581,0,'LifeDojo sold 11,000 student licenses in it\'s first 90 days in the market. We earned $2,500. With just one complete class. We will continue to recruit new instructors to build 30 classes by the mid-2014.\n\n1. LifeDojo will gain recognition and customers by selling classes on a variety of platforms like edmodo.com, chalkable.com and schoology.com\n2. Each market vertical has it\'s own \"communities\". We will identify the champions and advocates in each and recruit them to be champions of our brand',NULL,102,'2013-12-05 00:31:07','2013-12-05 00:31:07',6),(582,2,'1. Bringing on board quality instructors\n2. Ensuring course content is well written and the curriculum is solid\n3. Dynamic and beautiful platform to complement the amazing content',NULL,102,'2013-12-05 11:37:01','2013-12-05 00:45:09',7),(583,2,'Currently we have just one complete class. 60 days ago, we finalized 6 new instructors, and continue to recruit, interview and add instructors to build 30 classes by the mid-2014.\n\nThe 5-year trajectory of LifeDojo.com will result in over 250 online classes, over $70 million in revenue, and a massive positive impact on the world.\n\nLifeDojo is a scalable business with explosive growth potential and low overhead because once a class is created, it can be sold, resold and repackaged for 4-8 years before needing to be refreshed. If we build LifeDojo.com right the first time, and ensure quality content creation in years 1-3, the result will be sustainable revenue with very little overhead, allowing for larger sales teams and more comprehensive marketing efforts.',NULL,102,'2013-12-05 11:37:04','2013-12-05 00:39:36',9),(584,1,'3',NULL,104,'2013-12-05 06:07:27','2013-12-05 02:27:51',17),(585,1,'0. We aren\'t making money just yet so I can\'t give up my marketing clients yet.',NULL,100,'2013-12-05 06:07:45','2013-12-05 01:08:37',17),(586,1,'With iJar, teachers, student families and the general public can use our online interface for their purchases. Using affiliate marketing and our system, a portion of the money spent will go to a designated school district and a portion will go to the iJar participant. Tools and tips for sharing your iJar webpage will also be included to help raise even more money.',NULL,100,'2013-12-05 06:09:23','2013-12-05 00:40:08',1),(587,0,'Chris came up with tis idea over the course of the last 3 years',NULL,102,'2013-12-05 00:40:13','2013-12-05 00:40:13',10),(588,0,'Early 2012',NULL,102,'2013-12-05 00:40:25','2013-12-05 00:40:25',11),(589,1,'For the first two problems, at the moment, we are spending more time on Quality Control. For the future we are creating a process to make sure the Curriculum Director, who would be hired at a later stage, continues doing the same thing.\n\nWe have brought on board an experienced CTO who is working hard on the third problem.',NULL,102,'2013-12-05 06:18:08','2013-12-05 00:49:05',8),(590,1,'IJar is a simple solution to an ongoing problem for educators and students around the globe. IJar gives teachers, families and others an opportunity to make money in a passive way while also helping out local schools. \nI\'ve presented iJar to 13 school districts across 3 states, have had the plan reviewed by my state\'s Education Director, Governor Herbert, Mayor Corroon and thousands of parents. I have about 93% validation and pre-apporval from many districts.\nI\'m Jennifer, founder of iJar. My backstory is really that I love to learn, have the experience necessary and look forward to growing iJar to give back to teachers.\nAmenah is from Cairo and is in the US currently to go to business school. She understands the value (and cost) of a good education and currently works with me on some marketing accounts. She will be helping with administrative duties at iJar. I have additional members for the team but I just saw this opportunity - I didn\'t have time to get others listed.',NULL,100,'2013-12-05 06:18:15','2013-12-05 00:51:11',2),(591,0,'The company is a combination of an online marketplace and a business social networking platform and allow small  medium businesses & Enterprises to interact with professionals / freelancers / skilled workers.\nA dedicated platform for professionals / freelancers and businesses that allows them to build and manage business networks using tools such as UbizWeb Connections, Invitations, and Introductions, Access to knowledge using tools such as UbizWeb Groups, Network Updates, News, Answers etc.',NULL,104,'2013-12-05 00:49:10','2013-12-05 00:49:10',1),(592,0,'Yes',NULL,102,'2013-12-05 00:49:48','2013-12-05 00:49:48',12),(593,0,'Yes',NULL,102,'2013-12-05 00:50:08','2013-12-05 00:50:08',13),(594,0,'100',NULL,102,'2013-12-05 00:50:13','2013-12-05 00:50:13',14),(595,0,'800',NULL,102,'2013-12-05 00:51:57','2013-12-05 00:51:57',16),(596,0,'15000',NULL,102,'2013-12-05 00:52:03','2013-12-05 00:52:03',15),(597,0,'0',NULL,102,'2013-12-05 00:52:13','2013-12-05 00:52:13',20),(598,0,'2',NULL,102,'2013-12-05 00:52:34','2013-12-05 00:52:34',18),(599,1,'Raxx and I, met 18 years ago when I was looking for someone to design the website for the Booking Agency (Gianni Entertainment) I launched back in 2002. Since then we have been working together. Yesim and I met 2 years ago at an Entrepreneur event in Los Angeles and 6 months later I introduced her to Raxx as a potential co-founder of the company.\nThe visionary behind the concept (Ivan Gianni) had an idea of what he wanted, after which he some internal research and put in a lot of planning. The founder / visionary was really excited by the idea as he was interested in concepts that were connecting business-to-business. However, the concept thus evolved is applicable for both business-to-business, business-to-consumers and consumers-to-business. Also, the scalability of the business idea is the greatest advantage of the concept and is markedly different from the status quo!\nOur team has the right blend of dynamic, experience and youth, combined with managerial and technical skills.',NULL,104,'2013-12-05 06:24:01','2013-12-05 01:25:17',2),(600,0,'The idea is unique, though there are many fundraising programs. Some programs  that use a card similar to a grocer\'s discount card have been created but the impact is limited.\n Other fundraisers rely on extra purchases from parents, like cookie dough or wrapping paper, but the amount of money the school actually gets is ridiculously low and parents in this economy cannot keep buying overpriced items to support their schools and kids really shouldn\'t have to do door-to-door sales either.',NULL,100,'2013-12-05 00:54:28','2013-12-05 00:54:28',3),(601,0,'https://www.dropbox.com/s/er5mizjc6yvsbvo/LifeDojo%20Deck%20%28t%29.pdf',NULL,102,'2013-12-05 00:57:17','2013-12-05 00:57:17',19),(602,0,'We solve for education funding. ItJar is a long term program that has massive impact for teachers, student families and schools around the globe. Using existing purchases and subscription based sales, iJar will create passive streams of income for schools and participants. Teachers can get money back on supplies or share their iJar page across their social network to increase their iJar income, for example. ',NULL,100,'2013-12-05 00:57:31','2013-12-05 00:57:31',4),(603,0,'Yes',NULL,100,'2013-12-05 00:57:31','2013-12-05 00:57:31',5),(604,0,'through interactive materials that we provide to the participating school districts initially. Most districts we talked to also said they would not oppose an assembly at the beginning of the year and at the holiday season, but video would be more cost effective.\nI\'d also use PR and social media to spread the word.',NULL,100,'2013-12-05 00:59:15','2013-12-05 00:59:15',6),(605,0,'Building the back end website, finding time to go meet with additional districts and funding. I\'ve spent a lot of time and resources and need to push to the finish line.',NULL,100,'2013-12-05 01:00:10','2013-12-05 01:00:10',7),(606,0,'I\'ve been participating in Startup Weekend events and other local events that feature environments for programmers. I\'ve gotten a lot of great feedback this way and am a lot closer than I was prior. As for the time and money, work harder and smarter - it seems to do the trick.',NULL,100,'2013-12-05 01:01:21','2013-12-05 01:01:21',8),(607,0,'Initially it will require a lot of time to get schools involved, distribute materials and do the PR needed to spread the program across the country. Once it\'s a national program (approx 1.5-2 years), it will be time to find global partners (some I already have) to translate and help launch the program abroad. \nI\'ve done a similar business before and there is a bit of an unknown for customer service. I\'m not sure if we will need live help or if a forum would be appropriate. ',NULL,100,'2013-12-05 01:04:15','2013-12-05 01:04:15',9),(608,1,'2008-2009? It was a bit ahead of the market at the time.',NULL,100,'2013-12-05 06:34:33','2013-12-05 01:04:50',10),(609,0,'Last year when I saw education once again in the paper almost daily and it was mostly about budget cuts. Some included my elementary and I know iJar can help.',NULL,100,'2013-12-05 01:05:49','2013-12-05 01:05:49',11),(610,0,'Yes',NULL,100,'2013-12-05 01:05:54','2013-12-05 01:05:54',12),(611,0,'No',NULL,100,'2013-12-05 01:05:58','2013-12-05 01:05:58',13),(612,1,'We see how the platform can change peoples lives by just tweaking the way health and life skills are delivered, in an engaging and science-based way. \n\nWe have tested our business assumptions, proven that we can earn revenue, and have highly skilled founders and instructors capable of building a world-changing, explosive-growth company. All of us see a better future and make a small impact in our own way.',NULL,102,'2013-12-05 06:36:48','2013-12-05 01:12:20',21),(613,0,'I would guess 300 hours but I\'m not sure. I\'ve talked to developers and the main affiliate program and an MVP shouldn\'t be too difficult.',NULL,100,'2013-12-05 01:07:04','2013-12-05 01:07:04',16),(614,0,'20,000',NULL,100,'2013-12-05 01:07:48','2013-12-05 01:07:48',15),(615,0,'0',NULL,100,'2013-12-05 01:07:53','2013-12-05 01:07:53',20),(616,0,'1',NULL,100,'2013-12-05 01:08:46','2013-12-05 01:08:46',18),(617,0,'',NULL,100,'2013-12-05 01:09:14','2013-12-05 01:09:14',19),(618,0,'No',NULL,104,'2013-12-05 01:09:39','2013-12-05 01:09:39',5),(619,0,'It\'s needed and schools love it, teachers think it will work great. I feel almost like I to actually. ',NULL,100,'2013-12-05 01:10:22','2013-12-05 01:10:22',21),(620,0,'What UbizWeb is trying to achieve is much more ambitious:\nWe are integrating at once a job marketplace, where anyone can find skilled freelancers, services or businesses, while at the same time building a social network in which businesses can link to each other and form their own networks. \nProvides users with various tools to build and manage business networks\n',NULL,104,'2013-12-05 01:17:02','2013-12-05 01:17:02',4),(621,0,'Our team has the right blend of dynamic, experience and youth, combined with managerial and technical skills.\nEvery member of the team is working full-time on the company and is committed to working full-time and beyond.\nThe solution / marketplace is one of its kind and it is unique such that it caters to the skilled workers segment by connecting them with the people that need their services\n',NULL,104,'2013-12-05 01:20:35','2013-12-05 01:20:35',3),(622,1,'Sereal will be free for users. Initially, Sereal will acquire users by being incredibly simple to use and offering efficiency through the ability to search for multiple goods at once.\n\nSereal will retain users by consistently proving value in saving time and money. This will be accomplished by iterating with consumer demands: Sereal will recognize terminology and change results based on particular users. Additionally, the application will continue to become stronger by maintaining a database.',NULL,85,'2013-12-05 06:55:23','2013-12-05 01:25:37',6),(623,0,'The company will reach out to its target segment with the help of both online and offline marketing channels, i.e. Social Media, Search Engine Marketing, Search Engine Optimization, Limited Offline Promotion, YouTube Ads, E-mail marketing, Press Releases, Newsletters, Magazines, Article Marketing, Blog Marketing, etc.. However, the company will target freelancers from other freelancing websites, while businesses will be acquired using a phased region-by-region approach. \n',NULL,104,'2013-12-05 01:29:51','2013-12-05 01:29:51',6),(624,0,'$25',NULL,85,'2013-12-05 01:29:55','2013-12-05 01:29:55',14),(625,0,'2',NULL,85,'2013-12-05 01:30:01','2013-12-05 01:30:01',18),(626,0,'0',NULL,85,'2013-12-05 01:30:03','2013-12-05 01:30:03',20),(627,0,'We want to make peoples lives easier. We cant eliminate the need to buy groceries or the fact that the right soap is hard to find locally, but we can minimize the impact of these problems on consumers lives. For small business owners, we cant guarantee that consumers will buy products from a store, but we can ensure that the consumers know which products are sold in there. By clearing some of the fog in the market, we can make faster connections that benefit everyone. ',NULL,85,'2013-12-05 01:30:17','2013-12-05 01:30:17',21),(628,0,' Funding, Access to tools & skills and Strategic Advice ',NULL,104,'2013-12-05 01:33:43','2013-12-05 01:33:43',7),(629,0,'By enrolling to a program like 500Hrs or accelerator',NULL,104,'2013-12-05 01:49:41','2013-12-05 01:49:41',8),(630,3,'November 5, 2012',NULL,104,'2013-12-05 18:22:20','2013-12-05 02:16:38',10),(631,1,'November 23, 2012',NULL,104,'2013-12-05 07:23:17','2013-12-05 01:53:32',11),(632,0,'YR1 Completed accelerator program, launch first beta version, seek VC investment, establish corporative offices, hire team, reach $15M in revenue\nYR2 $20M Revenue\nYR3 $30M revenue',NULL,104,'2013-12-05 